190 bool AA::isNoSyncInst(Attributor &A, const Instruction &I,
191  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA) {
192  // We are looking for volatile instructions or non-relaxed atomics.
193  if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I)) {
194  if (CB->hasFnAttr(Attribute::NoSync))
195  return true;
196 
197  // Non-convergent and readnone imply nosync.
198  if (!CB->isConvergent() && !CB->mayReadOrWriteMemory())
199  return true;
200 
201  if (AANoSync::isNoSyncIntrinsic(&I))
202  return true;
203 
204  const auto &NoSyncAA = A.getAAFor<AANoSync>(
205  QueryingAA, IRPosition::callsite_function(*CB), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
206  return NoSyncAA.isAssumedNoSync();
207  }
208 
209  if (!I.mayReadOrWriteMemory())
210  return true;
211 
212  return !I.isVolatile() && !AANoSync::isNonRelaxedAtomic(&I);
213 }

225 Constant *AA::getInitialValueForObj(Value &Obj, Type &Ty,
226  const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
227  const DataLayout &DL,
228  AA::RangeTy *RangePtr) {
229  if (isa<AllocaInst>(Obj))
230  return UndefValue::get(&Ty);
231  if (Constant *Init = getInitialValueOfAllocation(&Obj, TLI, &Ty))
232  return Init;
233  auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(&Obj);
234  if (!GV)
235  return nullptr;
236  if (!GV->hasLocalLinkage() && !(GV->isConstant() && GV->hasInitializer()))
237  return nullptr;
238  if (!GV->hasInitializer())
239  return UndefValue::get(&Ty);
240 
241  if (RangePtr && !RangePtr->offsetOrSizeAreUnknown()) {
242  APInt Offset = APInt(64, RangePtr->Offset);
243  return ConstantFoldLoadFromConst(GV->getInitializer(), &Ty, Offset, DL);
244  }
245 
246  return ConstantFoldLoadFromUniformValue(GV->getInitializer(), &Ty);
247 }

249 bool AA::isValidInScope(const Value &V, const Function *Scope) {
250  if (isa<Constant>(V))
251  return true;
252  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&V))
253  return I->getFunction() == Scope;
254  if (auto *A = dyn_cast<Argument>(&V))
255  return A->getParent() == Scope;
256  return false;
257 }

259 bool AA::isValidAtPosition(const AA::ValueAndContext &VAC,
260  InformationCache &InfoCache) {
261  if (isa<Constant>(VAC.getValue()) || VAC.getValue() == VAC.getCtxI())
262  return true;
263  const Function *Scope = nullptr;
264  const Instruction *CtxI = VAC.getCtxI();
265  if (CtxI)
266  Scope = CtxI->getFunction();
267  if (auto *A = dyn_cast<Argument>(VAC.getValue()))
268  return A->getParent() == Scope;
269  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(VAC.getValue())) {
270  if (I->getFunction() == Scope) {
271  if (const DominatorTree *DT =
272  InfoCache.getAnalysisResultForFunction<DominatorTreeAnalysis>(
273  *Scope))
274  return DT->dominates(I, CtxI);
275  // Local dominance check mostly for the old PM passes.
276  if (CtxI && I->getParent() == CtxI->getParent())
277  return llvm::any_of(
278  make_range(I->getIterator(), I->getParent()->end()),
279  [&](const Instruction &AfterI) { return &AfterI == CtxI; });
280  }
281  }
282  return false;
283 }

285 Value *AA::getWithType(Value &V, Type &Ty) {
286  if (V.getType() == &Ty)
287  return &V;
288  if (isa<PoisonValue>(V))
289  return PoisonValue::get(&Ty);
290  if (isa<UndefValue>(V))
291  return UndefValue::get(&Ty);
292  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(&V)) {
293  if (C->isNullValue())
294  return Constant::getNullValue(&Ty);
295  if (C->getType()->isPointerTy() && Ty.isPointerTy())
296  return ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(C, &Ty);
297  if (C->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() >= Ty.getPrimitiveSizeInBits()) {
298  if (C->getType()->isIntegerTy() && Ty.isIntegerTy())
299  return ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, &Ty, /* OnlyIfReduced */ true);
300  if (C->getType()->isFloatingPointTy() && Ty.isFloatingPointTy())
301  return ConstantExpr::getFPTrunc(C, &Ty, /* OnlyIfReduced */ true);
302  }
303  }
304  return nullptr;
305 }

307 std::optional<Value *>
308 AA::combineOptionalValuesInAAValueLatice(const std::optional<Value *> &A,
309  const std::optional<Value *> &B,
310  Type *Ty) {
311  if (A == B)
312  return A;
313  if (!B)
314  return A;
315  if (*B == nullptr)
316  return nullptr;
317  if (!A)
318  return Ty ? getWithType(**B, *Ty) : nullptr;
319  if (*A == nullptr)
320  return nullptr;
321  if (!Ty)
322  Ty = (*A)->getType();
323  if (isa_and_nonnull<UndefValue>(*A))
324  return getWithType(**B, *Ty);
325  if (isa<UndefValue>(*B))
326  return A;
327  if (*A && *B && *A == getWithType(**B, *Ty))
328  return A;
329  return nullptr;
330 }

332 template <bool IsLoad, typename Ty>
333 static bool getPotentialCopiesOfMemoryValue(
334  Attributor &A, Ty &I, SmallSetVector<Value *, 4> &PotentialCopies,
335  SmallSetVector<Instruction *, 4> &PotentialValueOrigins,
336  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA, bool &UsedAssumedInformation,
337  bool OnlyExact) {
338  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying to determine the potential copies of " << I
339  << " (only exact: " << OnlyExact << ")\n";);
340 
341  Value &Ptr = *I.getPointerOperand();
342  // Containers to remember the pointer infos and new copies while we are not
343  // sure that we can find all of them. If we abort we want to avoid spurious
344  // dependences and potential copies in the provided container.
345  SmallVector<const AAPointerInfo *> PIs;
346  SmallVector<Value *> NewCopies;
347  SmallVector<Instruction *> NewCopyOrigins;
348 
349  const auto *TLI =
350  A.getInfoCache().getTargetLibraryInfoForFunction(*I.getFunction());
351 
352  auto Pred = [&](Value &Obj) {
353  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Visit underlying object " << Obj << "\n");
354  if (isa<UndefValue>(&Obj))
355  return true;
356  if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(&Obj)) {
357  // A null pointer access can be undefined but any offset from null may
358  // be OK. We do not try to optimize the latter.
359  if (!NullPointerIsDefined(I.getFunction(),
360  Ptr.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()) &&
361  A.getAssumedSimplified(Ptr, QueryingAA, UsedAssumedInformation,
362  AA::Interprocedural) == &Obj)
363  return true;
364  LLVM_DEBUG(
365  dbgs() << "Underlying object is a valid nullptr, giving up.\n";);
366  return false;
367  }
368  // TODO: Use assumed noalias return.
369  if (!isa<AllocaInst>(&Obj) && !isa<GlobalVariable>(&Obj) &&
370  !(IsLoad ? isAllocationFn(&Obj, TLI) : isNoAliasCall(&Obj))) {
371  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Underlying object is not supported yet: " << Obj
372  << "\n";);
373  return false;
374  }
375  if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(&Obj))
376  if (!GV->hasLocalLinkage() &&
377  !(GV->isConstant() && GV->hasInitializer())) {
378  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Underlying object is global with external "
379  "linkage, not supported yet: "
380  << Obj << "\n";);
381  return false;
382  }
383 
384  bool NullOnly = true;
385  bool NullRequired = false;
386  auto CheckForNullOnlyAndUndef = [&](std::optional<Value *> V,
387  bool IsExact) {
388  if (!V || *V == nullptr)
389  NullOnly = false;
390  else if (isa<UndefValue>(*V))
391  /* No op */;
392  else if (isa<Constant>(*V) && cast<Constant>(*V)->isNullValue())
393  NullRequired = !IsExact;
394  else
395  NullOnly = false;
396  };
397 
398  auto CheckAccess = [&](const AAPointerInfo::Access &Acc, bool IsExact) {
399  if ((IsLoad && !Acc.isWriteOrAssumption()) || (!IsLoad && !Acc.isRead()))
400  return true;
401  if (IsLoad && Acc.isWrittenValueYetUndetermined())
402  return true;
403  CheckForNullOnlyAndUndef(Acc.getContent(), IsExact);
404  if (OnlyExact && !IsExact && !NullOnly &&
405  !isa_and_nonnull<UndefValue>(Acc.getWrittenValue())) {
406  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Non exact access " << *Acc.getRemoteInst()
407  << ", abort!\n");
408  return false;
409  }
410  if (NullRequired && !NullOnly) {
411  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Required all `null` accesses due to non exact "
412  "one, however found non-null one: "
413  << *Acc.getRemoteInst() << ", abort!\n");
414  return false;
415  }
416  if (IsLoad) {
417  assert(isa<LoadInst>(I) && "Expected load or store instruction only!");
418  if (!Acc.isWrittenValueUnknown()) {
419  NewCopies.push_back(Acc.getWrittenValue());
420  NewCopyOrigins.push_back(Acc.getRemoteInst());
421  return true;
422  }
423  auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(Acc.getRemoteInst());
424  if (!SI) {
425  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Underlying object written through a non-store "
426  "instruction not supported yet: "
427  << *Acc.getRemoteInst() << "\n";);
428  return false;
429  }
430  NewCopies.push_back(SI->getValueOperand());
431  NewCopyOrigins.push_back(SI);
432  } else {
433  assert(isa<StoreInst>(I) && "Expected load or store instruction only!");
434  auto *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(Acc.getRemoteInst());
435  if (!LI && OnlyExact) {
436  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Underlying object read through a non-load "
437  "instruction not supported yet: "
438  << *Acc.getRemoteInst() << "\n";);
439  return false;
440  }
441  NewCopies.push_back(Acc.getRemoteInst());
442  }
443  return true;
444  };
445 
446  // If the value has been written to we don't need the initial value of the
447  // object.
448  bool HasBeenWrittenTo = false;
449 
450  AA::RangeTy Range;
451  auto &PI = A.getAAFor<AAPointerInfo>(QueryingAA, IRPosition::value(Obj),
452  DepClassTy::NONE);
453  if (!PI.forallInterferingAccesses(A, QueryingAA, I,
454  /* FindInterferingWrites */ IsLoad,
455  /* FindInterferingReads */ !IsLoad,
456  CheckAccess, HasBeenWrittenTo, Range)) {
457  LLVM_DEBUG(
458  dbgs()
459  << "Failed to verify all interfering accesses for underlying object: "
460  << Obj << "\n");
461  return false;
462  }
463 
464  if (IsLoad && !HasBeenWrittenTo && !Range.isUnassigned()) {
465  const DataLayout &DL = A.getDataLayout();
466  Value *InitialValue =
467  AA::getInitialValueForObj(Obj, *I.getType(), TLI, DL, &Range);
468  if (!InitialValue) {
469  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Could not determine required initial value of "
470  "underlying object, abort!\n");
471  return false;
472  }
473  CheckForNullOnlyAndUndef(InitialValue, /* IsExact */ true);
474  if (NullRequired && !NullOnly) {
475  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Non exact access but initial value that is not "
476  "null or undef, abort!\n");
477  return false;
478  }
479 
480  NewCopies.push_back(InitialValue);
481  NewCopyOrigins.push_back(nullptr);
482  }
483 
484  PIs.push_back(&PI);
485 
486  return true;
487  };
488 
489  const auto &AAUO = A.getAAFor<AAUnderlyingObjects>(
490  QueryingAA, IRPosition::value(Ptr), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
491  if (!AAUO.forallUnderlyingObjects(Pred)) {
492  LLVM_DEBUG(
493  dbgs() << "Underlying objects stored into could not be determined\n";);
494  return false;
495  }
496 
497  // Only if we were successful collection all potential copies we record
498  // dependences (on non-fix AAPointerInfo AAs). We also only then modify the
499  // given PotentialCopies container.
500  for (const auto *PI : PIs) {
501  if (!PI->getState().isAtFixpoint())
502  UsedAssumedInformation = true;
503  A.recordDependence(*PI, QueryingAA, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
504  }
505  PotentialCopies.insert(NewCopies.begin(), NewCopies.end());
506  PotentialValueOrigins.insert(NewCopyOrigins.begin(), NewCopyOrigins.end());
507 
508  return true;
509 }

531 static bool isAssumedReadOnlyOrReadNone(Attributor &A, const IRPosition &IRP,
532  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA,
533  bool RequireReadNone, bool &IsKnown) {
534 
535  IRPosition::Kind Kind = IRP.getPositionKind();
536  if (Kind == IRPosition::IRP_FUNCTION || Kind == IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE) {
537  const auto &MemLocAA =
538  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryLocation>(QueryingAA, IRP, DepClassTy::NONE);
539  if (MemLocAA.isAssumedReadNone()) {
540  IsKnown = MemLocAA.isKnownReadNone();
541  if (!IsKnown)
542  A.recordDependence(MemLocAA, QueryingAA, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
543  return true;
544  }
545  }
546 
547  const auto &MemBehaviorAA =
548  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(QueryingAA, IRP, DepClassTy::NONE);
549  if (MemBehaviorAA.isAssumedReadNone() ||
550  (!RequireReadNone && MemBehaviorAA.isAssumedReadOnly())) {
551  IsKnown = RequireReadNone ? MemBehaviorAA.isKnownReadNone()
552  : MemBehaviorAA.isKnownReadOnly();
553  if (!IsKnown)
554  A.recordDependence(MemBehaviorAA, QueryingAA, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
555  return true;
556  }
557 
558  return false;
559 }

561 bool AA::isAssumedReadOnly(Attributor &A, const IRPosition &IRP,
562  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA, bool &IsKnown) {
563  return isAssumedReadOnlyOrReadNone(A, IRP, QueryingAA,
564  /* RequireReadNone */ false, IsKnown);
565 }
566 bool AA::isAssumedReadNone(Attributor &A, const IRPosition &IRP,
567  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA, bool &IsKnown) {
568  return isAssumedReadOnlyOrReadNone(A, IRP, QueryingAA,
569  /* RequireReadNone */ true, IsKnown);
570 }

572 static bool
573 isPotentiallyReachable(Attributor &A, const Instruction &FromI,
574  const Instruction *ToI, const Function &ToFn,
575  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA,
576  const AA::InstExclusionSetTy *ExclusionSet,
577  std::function<bool(const Function &F)> GoBackwardsCB) {
578  LLVM_DEBUG({
579  dbgs() << "[AA] isPotentiallyReachable @" << ToFn.getName() << " from "
580  << FromI << " [GBCB: " << bool(GoBackwardsCB) << "][#ExS: "
581  << (ExclusionSet ? std::to_string(ExclusionSet->size()) : "none")
582  << "]\n";
583  if (ExclusionSet)
584  for (auto *ES : *ExclusionSet)
585  dbgs() << *ES << "\n";
586  });
587 
588  // We know kernels (generally) cannot be called from within the module. Thus,
589  // for reachability we would need to step back from a kernel which would allow
590  // us to reach anything anyway. Even if a kernel is invoked from another
591  // kernel, values like allocas and shared memory are not accessible. We
592  // implicitly check for this situation to avoid costly lookups.
593  if (GoBackwardsCB && &ToFn != FromI.getFunction() &&
594  !GoBackwardsCB(*FromI.getFunction()) && ToFn.hasFnAttribute("kernel") &&
595  FromI.getFunction()->hasFnAttribute("kernel")) {
596  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] assume kernel cannot be reached from within the "
597  "module; success\n";);
598  return false;
599  }
600 
601  // If we can go arbitrarily backwards we will eventually reach an entry point
602  // that can reach ToI. Only if a set of blocks through which we cannot go is
603  // provided, or once we track internal functions not accessible from the
604  // outside, it makes sense to perform backwards analysis in the absence of a
605  // GoBackwardsCB.
606  if (!GoBackwardsCB && !ExclusionSet) {
607  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] check @" << ToFn.getName() << " from " << FromI
608  << " is not checked backwards and does not have an "
609  "exclusion set, abort\n");
610  return true;
611  }
612 
613  SmallPtrSet<const Instruction *, 8> Visited;
614  SmallVector<const Instruction *> Worklist;
615  Worklist.push_back(&FromI);
616 
617  while (!Worklist.empty()) {
618  const Instruction *CurFromI = Worklist.pop_back_val();
619  if (!Visited.insert(CurFromI).second)
620  continue;
621 
622  const Function *FromFn = CurFromI->getFunction();
623  if (FromFn == &ToFn) {
624  if (!ToI)
625  return true;
626  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] check " << *ToI << " from " << *CurFromI
627  << " intraprocedurally\n");
628  const auto &ReachabilityAA = A.getAAFor<AAIntraFnReachability>(
629  QueryingAA, IRPosition::function(ToFn), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
630  bool Result =
631  ReachabilityAA.isAssumedReachable(A, *CurFromI, *ToI, ExclusionSet);
632  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] " << *CurFromI << " "
633  << (Result ? "can potentially " : "cannot ") << "reach "
634  << *ToI << " [Intra]\n");
635  if (Result)
636  return true;
637  }
638 
639  bool Result = true;
640  if (!ToFn.isDeclaration() && ToI) {
641  const auto &ToReachabilityAA = A.getAAFor<AAIntraFnReachability>(
642  QueryingAA, IRPosition::function(ToFn), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
643  const Instruction &EntryI = ToFn.getEntryBlock().front();
644  Result =
645  ToReachabilityAA.isAssumedReachable(A, EntryI, *ToI, ExclusionSet);
646  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] Entry " << EntryI << " of @" << ToFn.getName()
647  << " " << (Result ? "can potentially " : "cannot ")
648  << "reach @" << *ToI << " [ToFn]\n");
649  }
650 
651  if (Result) {
652  // The entry of the ToFn can reach the instruction ToI. If the current
653  // instruction is already known to reach the ToFn.
654  const auto &FnReachabilityAA = A.getAAFor<AAInterFnReachability>(
655  QueryingAA, IRPosition::function(*FromFn), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
656  Result = FnReachabilityAA.instructionCanReach(A, *CurFromI, ToFn,
657  ExclusionSet);
658  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] " << *CurFromI << " in @" << FromFn->getName()
659  << " " << (Result ? "can potentially " : "cannot ")
660  << "reach @" << ToFn.getName() << " [FromFn]\n");
661  if (Result)
662  return true;
663  }
664 
665  // TODO: Check assumed nounwind.
666  const auto &ReachabilityAA = A.getAAFor<AAIntraFnReachability>(
667  QueryingAA, IRPosition::function(*FromFn), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
668  auto ReturnInstCB = [&](Instruction &Ret) {
669  bool Result =
670  ReachabilityAA.isAssumedReachable(A, *CurFromI, Ret, ExclusionSet);
671  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA][Ret] " << *CurFromI << " "
672  << (Result ? "can potentially " : "cannot ") << "reach "
673  << Ret << " [Intra]\n");
674  return !Result;
675  };
676 
677  // Check if we can reach returns.
678  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
679  if (A.checkForAllInstructions(ReturnInstCB, FromFn, QueryingAA,
680  {Instruction::Ret}, UsedAssumedInformation)) {
681  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] No return is reachable, done\n");
682  continue;
683  }
684 
685  if (!GoBackwardsCB) {
686  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] check @" << ToFn.getName() << " from " << FromI
687  << " is not checked backwards, abort\n");
688  return true;
689  }
690 
691  // If we do not go backwards from the FromFn we are done here and so far we
692  // could not find a way to reach ToFn/ToI.
693  if (!GoBackwardsCB(*FromFn))
694  continue;
695 
696  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Stepping backwards to the call sites of @"
697  << FromFn->getName() << "\n");
698 
699  auto CheckCallSite = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
700  CallBase *CB = ACS.getInstruction();
701  if (!CB)
702  return false;
703 
704  if (isa<InvokeInst>(CB))
705  return false;
706 
707  Instruction *Inst = CB->getNextNonDebugInstruction();
708  Worklist.push_back(Inst);
709  return true;
710  };
711 
712  Result = !A.checkForAllCallSites(CheckCallSite, *FromFn,
713  /* RequireAllCallSites */ true,
714  &QueryingAA, UsedAssumedInformation);
715  if (Result) {
716  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] stepping back to call sites from " << *CurFromI
717  << " in @" << FromFn->getName()
718  << " failed, give up\n");
719  return true;
720  }
721 
722  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] stepped back to call sites from " << *CurFromI
723  << " in @" << FromFn->getName()
724  << " worklist size is: " << Worklist.size() << "\n");
725  }
726  return false;
727 }

748 bool AA::isAssumedThreadLocalObject(Attributor &A, Value &Obj,
749  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA) {
750  if (isa<UndefValue>(Obj))
751  return true;
752  if (isa<AllocaInst>(Obj)) {
753  InformationCache &InfoCache = A.getInfoCache();
754  if (!InfoCache.stackIsAccessibleByOtherThreads()) {
755  LLVM_DEBUG(
756  dbgs() << "[AA] Object '" << Obj
757  << "' is thread local; stack objects are thread local.\n");
758  return true;
759  }
760  const auto &NoCaptureAA = A.getAAFor<AANoCapture>(
761  QueryingAA, IRPosition::value(Obj), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
762  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] Object '" << Obj << "' is "
763  << (NoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCapture() ? "" : "not")
764  << " thread local; "
765  << (NoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCapture() ? "non-" : "")
766  << "captured stack object.\n");
767  return NoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCapture();
768  }
769  if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(&Obj)) {
770  if (GV->isConstant()) {
771  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] Object '" << Obj
772  << "' is thread local; constant global\n");
773  return true;
774  }
775  if (GV->isThreadLocal()) {
776  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] Object '" << Obj
777  << "' is thread local; thread local global\n");
778  return true;
779  }
780  }
781 
782  if (A.getInfoCache().targetIsGPU()) {
783  if (Obj.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
784  (int)AA::GPUAddressSpace::Local) {
785  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] Object '" << Obj
786  << "' is thread local; GPU local memory\n");
787  return true;
788  }
789  if (Obj.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
790  (int)AA::GPUAddressSpace::Constant) {
791  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] Object '" << Obj
792  << "' is thread local; GPU constant memory\n");
793  return true;
794  }
795  }
796 
797  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] Object '" << Obj << "' is not thread local\n");
798  return false;
799 }

801 bool AA::isPotentiallyAffectedByBarrier(Attributor &A, const Instruction &I,
802  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA) {
803  if (!I.mayHaveSideEffects() && !I.mayReadFromMemory())
804  return false;
805 
806  SmallSetVector<const Value *, 8> Ptrs;
807 
808  auto AddLocationPtr = [&](std::optional<MemoryLocation> Loc) {
809  if (!Loc || !Loc->Ptr) {
810  LLVM_DEBUG(
811  dbgs() << "[AA] Access to unknown location; -> requires barriers\n");
812  return false;
813  }
814  Ptrs.insert(Loc->Ptr);
815  return true;
816  };
817 
818  if (const MemIntrinsic *MI = dyn_cast<MemIntrinsic>(&I)) {
819  if (!AddLocationPtr(MemoryLocation::getForDest(MI)))
820  return true;
821  if (const MemTransferInst *MTI = dyn_cast<MemTransferInst>(&I))
822  if (!AddLocationPtr(MemoryLocation::getForSource(MTI)))
823  return true;
824  } else if (!AddLocationPtr(MemoryLocation::getOrNone(&I)))
825  return true;
826 
827  return isPotentiallyAffectedByBarrier(A, Ptrs.getArrayRef(), QueryingAA, &I);
828 }
829 
830 bool AA::isPotentiallyAffectedByBarrier(Attributor &A,
831  ArrayRef<const Value *> Ptrs,
832  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA,
833  const Instruction *CtxI) {
834  for (const Value *Ptr : Ptrs) {
835  if (!Ptr) {
836  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] nullptr; -> requires barriers\n");
837  return true;
838  }
839 
840  auto Pred = [&](Value &Obj) {
841  if (AA::isAssumedThreadLocalObject(A, Obj, QueryingAA))
842  return true;
843  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AA] Access to '" << Obj << "' via '" << *Ptr
844  << "'; -> requires barrier\n");
845  return false;
846  };
847 
848  const auto &UnderlyingObjsAA = A.getAAFor<AAUnderlyingObjects>(
849  QueryingAA, IRPosition::value(*Ptr), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
850  if (!UnderlyingObjsAA.forallUnderlyingObjects(Pred))
851  return true;
852  }
853  return false;
854 }

856 /// Return true if \p New is equal or worse than \p Old.
857 static bool isEqualOrWorse(const Attribute &New, const Attribute &Old) {
858  if (!Old.isIntAttribute())
859  return true;
860 
861  return Old.getValueAsInt() >= New.getValueAsInt();
862 }
863 
864 /// Return true if the information provided by \p Attr was added to the
865 /// attribute list \p Attrs. This is only the case if it was not already present
866 /// in \p Attrs at the position describe by \p PK and \p AttrIdx.
867 static bool addIfNotExistent(LLVMContext &Ctx, const Attribute &Attr,
868  AttributeList &Attrs, int AttrIdx,
869  bool ForceReplace = false) {
870 
871  if (Attr.isEnumAttribute()) {
872  Attribute::AttrKind Kind = Attr.getKindAsEnum();
873  if (Attrs.hasAttributeAtIndex(AttrIdx, Kind))
874  if (!ForceReplace &&
875  isEqualOrWorse(Attr, Attrs.getAttributeAtIndex(AttrIdx, Kind)))
876  return false;
877  Attrs = Attrs.addAttributeAtIndex(Ctx, AttrIdx, Attr);
878  return true;
879  }
880  if (Attr.isStringAttribute()) {
881  StringRef Kind = Attr.getKindAsString();
882  if (Attrs.hasAttributeAtIndex(AttrIdx, Kind))
883  if (!ForceReplace &&
884  isEqualOrWorse(Attr, Attrs.getAttributeAtIndex(AttrIdx, Kind)))
885  return false;
886  Attrs = Attrs.addAttributeAtIndex(Ctx, AttrIdx, Attr);
887  return true;
888  }
889  if (Attr.isIntAttribute()) {
890  Attribute::AttrKind Kind = Attr.getKindAsEnum();
891  if (Attrs.hasAttributeAtIndex(AttrIdx, Kind))
892  if (!ForceReplace &&
893  isEqualOrWorse(Attr, Attrs.getAttributeAtIndex(AttrIdx, Kind)))
894  return false;
895  Attrs = Attrs.removeAttributeAtIndex(Ctx, AttrIdx, Kind);
896  Attrs = Attrs.addAttributeAtIndex(Ctx, AttrIdx, Attr);
897  return true;
898  }
899 
900  llvm_unreachable("Expected enum or string attribute!");
901 }

903 Argument *IRPosition::getAssociatedArgument() const {
904  if (getPositionKind() == IRP_ARGUMENT)
905  return cast<Argument>(&getAnchorValue());
906 
907  // Not an Argument and no argument number means this is not a call site
908  // argument, thus we cannot find a callback argument to return.
909  int ArgNo = getCallSiteArgNo();
910  if (ArgNo < 0)
911  return nullptr;
912 
913  // Use abstract call sites to make the connection between the call site
914  // values and the ones in callbacks. If a callback was found that makes use
915  // of the underlying call site operand, we want the corresponding callback
916  // callee argument and not the direct callee argument.
917  std::optional<Argument *> CBCandidateArg;
918  SmallVector<const Use *, 4> CallbackUses;
919  const auto &CB = cast<CallBase>(getAnchorValue());
920  AbstractCallSite::getCallbackUses(CB, CallbackUses);
921  for (const Use *U : CallbackUses) {
922  AbstractCallSite ACS(U);
923  assert(ACS && ACS.isCallbackCall());
924  if (!ACS.getCalledFunction())
925  continue;
926 
927  for (unsigned u = 0, e = ACS.getNumArgOperands(); u < e; u++) {
928 
929  // Test if the underlying call site operand is argument number u of the
930  // callback callee.
931  if (ACS.getCallArgOperandNo(u) != ArgNo)
932  continue;
933 
934  assert(ACS.getCalledFunction()->arg_size() > u &&
935  "ACS mapped into var-args arguments!");
936  if (CBCandidateArg) {
937  CBCandidateArg = nullptr;
938  break;
939  }
940  CBCandidateArg = ACS.getCalledFunction()->getArg(u);
941  }
942  }
943 
944  // If we found a unique callback candidate argument, return it.
945  if (CBCandidateArg && *CBCandidateArg)
946  return *CBCandidateArg;
947 
948  // If no callbacks were found, or none used the underlying call site operand
949  // exclusively, use the direct callee argument if available.
950  const Function *Callee = CB.getCalledFunction();
951  if (Callee && Callee->arg_size() > unsigned(ArgNo))
952  return Callee->getArg(ArgNo);
953 
954  return nullptr;
955 }

957 ChangeStatus AbstractAttribute::update(Attributor &A) {
958  ChangeStatus HasChanged = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
959  if (getState().isAtFixpoint())
960  return HasChanged;
961 
962  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Update: " << *this << "\n");
963 
964  HasChanged = updateImpl(A);
965 
966  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Update " << HasChanged << " " << *this
967  << "\n");
968 
969  return HasChanged;
970 }

972 ChangeStatus
973 IRAttributeManifest::manifestAttrs(Attributor &A, const IRPosition &IRP,
974  const ArrayRef<Attribute> &DeducedAttrs,
975  bool ForceReplace) {
976  Function *ScopeFn = IRP.getAnchorScope();
977  IRPosition::Kind PK = IRP.getPositionKind();
978 
979  // In the following some generic code that will manifest attributes in
980  // DeducedAttrs if they improve the current IR. Due to the different
981  // annotation positions we use the underlying AttributeList interface.
982 
983  AttributeList Attrs;
984  switch (PK) {
985  case IRPosition::IRP_INVALID:
986  case IRPosition::IRP_FLOAT:
987  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
988  case IRPosition::IRP_ARGUMENT:
989  case IRPosition::IRP_FUNCTION:
990  case IRPosition::IRP_RETURNED:
991  Attrs = ScopeFn->getAttributes();
992  break;
993  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE:
994  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE_RETURNED:
995  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE_ARGUMENT:
996  Attrs = cast<CallBase>(IRP.getAnchorValue()).getAttributes();
997  break;
998  }
999 
1000  ChangeStatus HasChanged = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
1001  LLVMContext &Ctx = IRP.getAnchorValue().getContext();
1002  for (const Attribute &Attr : DeducedAttrs) {
1003  if (!addIfNotExistent(Ctx, Attr, Attrs, IRP.getAttrIdx(), ForceReplace))
1004  continue;
1005 
1006  HasChanged = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
1007  }
1008 
1009  if (HasChanged == ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED)
1010  return HasChanged;
1011 
1012  switch (PK) {
1013  case IRPosition::IRP_ARGUMENT:
1014  case IRPosition::IRP_FUNCTION:
1015  case IRPosition::IRP_RETURNED:
1016  ScopeFn->setAttributes(Attrs);
1017  break;
1018  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE:
1019  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE_RETURNED:
1020  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE_ARGUMENT:
1021  cast<CallBase>(IRP.getAnchorValue()).setAttributes(Attrs);
1022  break;
1023  case IRPosition::IRP_INVALID:
1024  case IRPosition::IRP_FLOAT:
1025  break;
1026  }
1027 
1028  return HasChanged;
1029 }

1035 SubsumingPositionIterator::SubsumingPositionIterator(const IRPosition &IRP) {
1036  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRP);
1037 
1038  // Helper to determine if operand bundles on a call site are benin or
1039  // potentially problematic. We handle only llvm.assume for now.
1040  auto CanIgnoreOperandBundles = [](const CallBase &CB) {
1041  return (isa<IntrinsicInst>(CB) &&
1042  cast<IntrinsicInst>(CB).getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic ::assume);
1043  };
1044 
1045  const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&IRP.getAnchorValue());
1046  switch (IRP.getPositionKind()) {
1047  case IRPosition::IRP_INVALID:
1048  case IRPosition::IRP_FLOAT:
1049  case IRPosition::IRP_FUNCTION:
1050  return;
1051  case IRPosition::IRP_ARGUMENT:
1052  case IRPosition::IRP_RETURNED:
1053  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::function(*IRP.getAnchorScope()));
1054  return;
1055  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE:
1056  assert(CB && "Expected call site!");
1057  // TODO: We need to look at the operand bundles similar to the redirection
1058  // in CallBase.
1059  if (!CB->hasOperandBundles() || CanIgnoreOperandBundles(*CB))
1060  if (const Function *Callee = CB->getCalledFunction())
1061  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::function(*Callee));
1062  return;
1063  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE_RETURNED:
1064  assert(CB && "Expected call site!");
1065  // TODO: We need to look at the operand bundles similar to the redirection
1066  // in CallBase.
1067  if (!CB->hasOperandBundles() || CanIgnoreOperandBundles(*CB)) {
1068  if (const Function *Callee = CB->getCalledFunction()) {
1069  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::returned(*Callee));
1070  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::function(*Callee));
1071  for (const Argument &Arg : Callee->args())
1072  if (Arg.hasReturnedAttr()) {
1073  IRPositions.emplace_back(
1074  IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, Arg.getArgNo()));
1075  IRPositions.emplace_back(
1076  IRPosition::value(*CB->getArgOperand(Arg.getArgNo())));
1077  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::argument(Arg));
1078  }
1079  }
1080  }
1081  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::callsite_function(*CB));
1082  return;
1083  case IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE_ARGUMENT: {
1084  assert(CB && "Expected call site!");
1085  // TODO: We need to look at the operand bundles similar to the redirection
1086  // in CallBase.
1087  if (!CB->hasOperandBundles() || CanIgnoreOperandBundles(*CB)) {
1088  const Function *Callee = CB->getCalledFunction();
1089  if (Callee) {
1090  if (Argument *Arg = IRP.getAssociatedArgument())
1091  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::argument(*Arg));
1092  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::function(*Callee));
1093  }
1094  }
1095  IRPositions.emplace_back(IRPosition::value(IRP.getAssociatedValue()));
1096  return;
1097  }
1098  }
1099 }

1101 bool IRPosition::hasAttr(ArrayRef<Attribute::AttrKind> AKs,
1102  bool IgnoreSubsumingPositions, Attributor *A) const {
1103  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> Attrs;
1104  for (const IRPosition &EquivIRP : SubsumingPositionIterator(*this)) {
1105  for (Attribute::AttrKind AK : AKs)
1106  if (EquivIRP.getAttrsFromIRAttr(AK, Attrs))
1107  return true;
1108  // The first position returned by the SubsumingPositionIterator is
1109  // always the position itself. If we ignore subsuming positions we
1110  // are done after the first iteration.
1111  if (IgnoreSubsumingPositions)
1112  break;
1113  }
1114  if (A)
1115  for (Attribute::AttrKind AK : AKs)
1116  if (getAttrsFromAssumes(AK, Attrs, *A))
1117  return true;
1118  return false;
1119 }

1121 void IRPosition::getAttrs(ArrayRef<Attribute::AttrKind> AKs,
1122  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &Attrs,
1123  bool IgnoreSubsumingPositions, Attributor *A) const {
1124  for (const IRPosition &EquivIRP : SubsumingPositionIterator(*this)) {
1125  for (Attribute::AttrKind AK : AKs)
1126  EquivIRP.getAttrsFromIRAttr(AK, Attrs);
1127  // The first position returned by the SubsumingPositionIterator is
1128  // always the position itself. If we ignore subsuming positions we
1129  // are done after the first iteration.
1130  if (IgnoreSubsumingPositions)
1131  break;
1132  }
1133  if (A)
1134  for (Attribute::AttrKind AK : AKs)
1135  getAttrsFromAssumes(AK, Attrs, *A);
1136 }

1138 bool IRPosition::getAttrsFromIRAttr(Attribute::AttrKind AK,
1139  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &Attrs) const {
1140  if (getPositionKind() == IRP_INVALID || getPositionKind() == IRP_FLOAT)
1141  return false;
1142 
1143  AttributeList AttrList;
1144  if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&getAnchorValue()))
1145  AttrList = CB->getAttributes();
1146  else
1147  AttrList = getAssociatedFunction()->getAttributes();
1148 
1149  bool HasAttr = AttrList.hasAttributeAtIndex(getAttrIdx(), AK);
1150  if (HasAttr)
1151  Attrs.push_back(AttrList.getAttributeAtIndex(getAttrIdx(), AK));
1152  return HasAttr;
1153 }
1154 
1155 bool IRPosition::getAttrsFromAssumes(Attribute::AttrKind AK,
1156  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &Attrs,
1157  Attributor &A) const {
1158  assert(getPositionKind() != IRP_INVALID && "Did expect a valid position!");
1159  Value &AssociatedValue = getAssociatedValue();
1160 
1161  const Assume2KnowledgeMap &A2K =
1162  A.getInfoCache().getKnowledgeMap().lookup({&AssociatedValue, AK});
1163 
1164  // Check if we found any potential assume use, if not we don't need to create
1165  // explorer iterators.
1166  if (A2K.empty())
1167  return false;
1168 
1169  LLVMContext &Ctx = AssociatedValue.getContext();
1170  unsigned AttrsSize = Attrs.size();
1171  MustBeExecutedContextExplorer &Explorer =
1172  A.getInfoCache().getMustBeExecutedContextExplorer();
1173  auto EIt = Explorer.begin(getCtxI()), EEnd = Explorer.end(getCtxI());
1174  for (const auto &It : A2K)
1175  if (Explorer.findInContextOf(It.first, EIt, EEnd))
1176  Attrs.push_back(Attribute::get(Ctx, AK, It.second.Max));
1177  return AttrsSize != Attrs.size();
1178 }
1179 
1180 void IRPosition::verify() {
1181 #ifdef EXPENSIVE_CHECKS
1182  switch (getPositionKind()) {
1183  case IRP_INVALID:
1184  assert((CBContext == nullptr) &&
1185  "Invalid position must not have CallBaseContext!");
1186  assert(!Enc.getOpaqueValue() &&
1187  "Expected a nullptr for an invalid position!");
1188  return;
1189  case IRP_FLOAT:
1190  assert((!isa<Argument>(&getAssociatedValue())) &&
1191  "Expected specialized kind for argument values!");
1192  return;
1193  case IRP_RETURNED:
1194  assert(isa<Function>(getAsValuePtr()) &&
1195  "Expected function for a 'returned' position!");
1196  assert(getAsValuePtr() == &getAssociatedValue() &&
1197  "Associated value mismatch!");
1198  return;
1199  case IRP_CALL_SITE_RETURNED:
1200  assert((CBContext == nullptr) &&
1201  "'call site returned' position must not have CallBaseContext!");
1202  assert((isa<CallBase>(getAsValuePtr())) &&
1203  "Expected call base for 'call site returned' position!");
1204  assert(getAsValuePtr() == &getAssociatedValue() &&
1205  "Associated value mismatch!");
1206  return;
1207  case IRP_CALL_SITE:
1208  assert((CBContext == nullptr) &&
1209  "'call site function' position must not have CallBaseContext!");
1210  assert((isa<CallBase>(getAsValuePtr())) &&
1211  "Expected call base for 'call site function' position!");
1212  assert(getAsValuePtr() == &getAssociatedValue() &&
1213  "Associated value mismatch!");
1214  return;
1215  case IRP_FUNCTION:
1216  assert(isa<Function>(getAsValuePtr()) &&
1217  "Expected function for a 'function' position!");
1218  assert(getAsValuePtr() == &getAssociatedValue() &&
1219  "Associated value mismatch!");
1220  return;
1221  case IRP_ARGUMENT:
1222  assert(isa<Argument>(getAsValuePtr()) &&
1223  "Expected argument for a 'argument' position!");
1224  assert(getAsValuePtr() == &getAssociatedValue() &&
1225  "Associated value mismatch!");
1226  return;
1227  case IRP_CALL_SITE_ARGUMENT: {
1228  assert((CBContext == nullptr) &&
1229  "'call site argument' position must not have CallBaseContext!");
1230  Use *U = getAsUsePtr();
1231  (void)U; // Silence unused variable warning.
1232  assert(U && "Expected use for a 'call site argument' position!");
1233  assert(isa<CallBase>(U->getUser()) &&
1234  "Expected call base user for a 'call site argument' position!");
1235  assert(cast<CallBase>(U->getUser())->isArgOperand(U) &&
1236  "Expected call base argument operand for a 'call site argument' "
1237  "position");
1238  assert(cast<CallBase>(U->getUser())->getArgOperandNo(U) ==
1239  unsigned(getCallSiteArgNo()) &&
1240  "Argument number mismatch!");
1241  assert(U->get() == &getAssociatedValue() && "Associated value mismatch!");
1242  return;
1243  }
1244  }
1245 #endif
1246 }

1248 std::optional<Constant *>
1249 Attributor::getAssumedConstant(const IRPosition &IRP,
1250  const AbstractAttribute &AA,
1251  bool &UsedAssumedInformation) {
1252  // First check all callbacks provided by outside AAs. If any of them returns
1253  // a non-null value that is different from the associated value, or
1254  // std::nullopt, we assume it's simplified.
1255  for (auto &CB : SimplificationCallbacks.lookup(IRP)) {
1256  std::optional<Value *> SimplifiedV = CB(IRP, &AA, UsedAssumedInformation);
1257  if (!SimplifiedV)
1258  return std::nullopt;
1259  if (isa_and_nonnull<Constant>(*SimplifiedV))
1260  return cast<Constant>(*SimplifiedV);
1261  return nullptr;
1262  }
1263  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(&IRP.getAssociatedValue()))
1264  return C;
1265  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
1266  if (getAssumedSimplifiedValues(IRP, &AA, Values,
1267  AA::ValueScope::Interprocedural,
1268  UsedAssumedInformation)) {
1269  if (Values.empty())
1270  return std::nullopt;
1271  if (auto *C = dyn_cast_or_null<Constant>(
1272  AAPotentialValues::getSingleValue(*this, AA, IRP, Values)))
1273  return C;
1274  }
1275  return nullptr;
1276 }
1277 
1278 std::optional<Value *> Attributor::getAssumedSimplified(
1279  const IRPosition &IRP, const AbstractAttribute *AA,
1280  bool &UsedAssumedInformation, AA::ValueScope S) {
1281  // First check all callbacks provided by outside AAs. If any of them returns
1282  // a non-null value that is different from the associated value, or
1283  // std::nullopt, we assume it's simplified.
1284  for (auto &CB : SimplificationCallbacks.lookup(IRP))
1285  return CB(IRP, AA, UsedAssumedInformation);
1286 
1287  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
1288  if (!getAssumedSimplifiedValues(IRP, AA, Values, S, UsedAssumedInformation))
1289  return &IRP.getAssociatedValue();
1290  if (Values.empty())
1291  return std::nullopt;
1292  if (AA)
1293  if (Value *V = AAPotentialValues::getSingleValue(*this, *AA, IRP, Values))
1294  return V;
1295  if (IRP.getPositionKind() == IRPosition::IRP_RETURNED ||
1296  IRP.getPositionKind() == IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE_RETURNED)
1297  return nullptr;
1298  return &IRP.getAssociatedValue();
1299 }
1300 
1301 bool Attributor::getAssumedSimplifiedValues(
1302  const IRPosition &IRP, const AbstractAttribute *AA,
1303  SmallVectorImpl<AA::ValueAndContext> &Values, AA::ValueScope S,
1304  bool &UsedAssumedInformation) {
1305  // First check all callbacks provided by outside AAs. If any of them returns
1306  // a non-null value that is different from the associated value, or
1307  // std::nullopt, we assume it's simplified.
1308  const auto &SimplificationCBs = SimplificationCallbacks.lookup(IRP);
1309  for (const auto &CB : SimplificationCBs) {
1310  std::optional<Value *> CBResult = CB(IRP, AA, UsedAssumedInformation);
1311  if (!CBResult.has_value())
1312  continue;
1313  Value *V = *CBResult;
1314  if (!V)
1315  return false;
1316  if ((S & AA::ValueScope::Interprocedural) ||
1317  AA::isValidInScope(*V, IRP.getAnchorScope()))
1318  Values.push_back(AA::ValueAndContext{*V, nullptr});
1319  else
1320  return false;
1321  }
1322  if (!SimplificationCBs.empty())
1323  return true;
1324 
1325  // If no high-level/outside simplification occurred, use AAPotentialValues.
1326  const auto &PotentialValuesAA =
1327  getOrCreateAAFor<AAPotentialValues>(IRP, AA, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
1328  if (!PotentialValuesAA.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(*this, Values, S))
1329  return false;
1330  UsedAssumedInformation |= !PotentialValuesAA.isAtFixpoint();
1331  return true;
1332 }

1334 std::optional<Value *> Attributor::translateArgumentToCallSiteContent(
1335  std::optional<Value *> V, CallBase &CB, const AbstractAttribute &AA,
1336  bool &UsedAssumedInformation) {
1337  if (!V)
1338  return V;
1339  if (*V == nullptr || isa<Constant>(*V))
1340  return V;
1341  if (auto *Arg = dyn_cast<Argument>(*V))
1342  if (CB.getCalledFunction() == Arg->getParent())
1343  if (!Arg->hasPointeeInMemoryValueAttr())
1344  return getAssumedSimplified(
1345  IRPosition::callsite_argument(CB, Arg->getArgNo()), AA,
1346  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Intraprocedural);
1347  return nullptr;
1348 }

1370 bool Attributor::isAssumedDead(const Use &U,
1371  const AbstractAttribute *QueryingAA,
1372  const AAIsDead *FnLivenessAA,
1373  bool &UsedAssumedInformation,
1374  bool CheckBBLivenessOnly, DepClassTy DepClass) {
1375  Instruction *UserI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
1376  if (!UserI)
1377  return isAssumedDead(IRPosition::value(*U.get()), QueryingAA, FnLivenessAA,
1378  UsedAssumedInformation, CheckBBLivenessOnly, DepClass);
1379 
1380  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(UserI)) {
1381  // For call site argument uses we can check if the argument is
1382  // unused/dead.
1383  if (CB->isArgOperand(&U)) {
1384  const IRPosition &CSArgPos =
1385  IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, CB->getArgOperandNo(&U));
1386  return isAssumedDead(CSArgPos, QueryingAA, FnLivenessAA,
1387  UsedAssumedInformation, CheckBBLivenessOnly,
1388  DepClass);
1389  }
1390  } else if (ReturnInst *RI = dyn_cast<ReturnInst>(UserI)) {
1391  const IRPosition &RetPos = IRPosition::returned(*RI->getFunction());
1392  return isAssumedDead(RetPos, QueryingAA, FnLivenessAA,
1393  UsedAssumedInformation, CheckBBLivenessOnly, DepClass);
1394  } else if (PHINode *PHI = dyn_cast<PHINode>(UserI)) {
1395  BasicBlock *IncomingBB = PHI->getIncomingBlock(U);
1396  return isAssumedDead(*IncomingBB->getTerminator(), QueryingAA, FnLivenessAA,
1397  UsedAssumedInformation, CheckBBLivenessOnly, DepClass);
1398  } else if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(UserI)) {
1399  if (!CheckBBLivenessOnly && SI->getPointerOperand() != U.get()) {
1400  const IRPosition IRP = IRPosition::inst(*SI);
1401  const AAIsDead &IsDeadAA =
1402  getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(IRP, QueryingAA, DepClassTy::NONE);
1403  if (IsDeadAA.isRemovableStore()) {
1404  if (QueryingAA)
1405  recordDependence(IsDeadAA, *QueryingAA, DepClass);
1406  if (!IsDeadAA.isKnown(AAIsDead::IS_REMOVABLE))
1407  UsedAssumedInformation = true;
1408  return true;
1409  }
1410  }
1411  }
1412 
1413  return isAssumedDead(IRPosition::inst(*UserI), QueryingAA, FnLivenessAA,
1414  UsedAssumedInformation, CheckBBLivenessOnly, DepClass);
1415 }
1416 
1417 bool Attributor::isAssumedDead(const Instruction &I,
1418  const AbstractAttribute *QueryingAA,
1419  const AAIsDead *FnLivenessAA,
1420  bool &UsedAssumedInformation,
1421  bool CheckBBLivenessOnly, DepClassTy DepClass,
1422  bool CheckForDeadStore) {
1423  const IRPosition::CallBaseContext *CBCtx =
1424  QueryingAA ? QueryingAA->getCallBaseContext() : nullptr;
1425 
1426  if (ManifestAddedBlocks.contains(I.getParent()))
1427  return false;
1428 
1429  const Function &F = *I.getFunction();
1430  if (!FnLivenessAA || FnLivenessAA->getAnchorScope() != &F)
1431  FnLivenessAA = &getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(IRPosition::function(F, CBCtx),
1432  QueryingAA, DepClassTy::NONE);
1433 
1434  // Don't use recursive reasoning.
1435  if (QueryingAA == FnLivenessAA)
1436  return false;
1437 
1438  // If we have a context instruction and a liveness AA we use it.
1439  if (CheckBBLivenessOnly ? FnLivenessAA->isAssumedDead(I.getParent())
1440  : FnLivenessAA->isAssumedDead(&I)) {
1441  if (QueryingAA)
1442  recordDependence(*FnLivenessAA, *QueryingAA, DepClass);
1443  if (!FnLivenessAA->isKnownDead(&I))
1444  UsedAssumedInformation = true;
1445  return true;
1446  }
1447 
1448  if (CheckBBLivenessOnly)
1449  return false;
1450 
1451  const IRPosition IRP = IRPosition::inst(I, CBCtx);
1452  const AAIsDead &IsDeadAA =
1453  getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(IRP, QueryingAA, DepClassTy::NONE);
1454 
1455  // Don't use recursive reasoning.
1456  if (QueryingAA == &IsDeadAA)
1457  return false;
1458 
1459  if (IsDeadAA.isAssumedDead()) {
1460  if (QueryingAA)
1461  recordDependence(IsDeadAA, *QueryingAA, DepClass);
1462  if (!IsDeadAA.isKnownDead())
1463  UsedAssumedInformation = true;
1464  return true;
1465  }
1466 
1467  if (CheckForDeadStore && isa<StoreInst>(I) && IsDeadAA.isRemovableStore()) {
1468  if (QueryingAA)
1469  recordDependence(IsDeadAA, *QueryingAA, DepClass);
1470  if (!IsDeadAA.isKnownDead())
1471  UsedAssumedInformation = true;
1472  return true;
1473  }
1474 
1475  return false;
1476 }
1477 
1478 bool Attributor::isAssumedDead(const IRPosition &IRP,
1479  const AbstractAttribute *QueryingAA,
1480  const AAIsDead *FnLivenessAA,
1481  bool &UsedAssumedInformation,
1482  bool CheckBBLivenessOnly, DepClassTy DepClass) {
1483  // Don't check liveness for constants, e.g. functions, used as (floating)
1484  // values since the context instruction and such is here meaningless.
1485  if (IRP.getPositionKind() == IRPosition::IRP_FLOAT &&
1486  isa<Constant>(IRP.getAssociatedValue())) {
1487  return false;
1488  }
1489 
1490  Instruction *CtxI = IRP.getCtxI();
1491  if (CtxI &&
1492  isAssumedDead(*CtxI, QueryingAA, FnLivenessAA, UsedAssumedInformation,
1493  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ true,
1494  CheckBBLivenessOnly ? DepClass : DepClassTy::OPTIONAL))
1495  return true;
1496 
1497  if (CheckBBLivenessOnly)
1498  return false;
1499 
1500  // If we haven't succeeded we query the specific liveness info for the IRP.
1501  const AAIsDead *IsDeadAA;
1502  if (IRP.getPositionKind() == IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE)
1503  IsDeadAA = &getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(
1504  IRPosition::callsite_returned(cast<CallBase>(IRP.getAssociatedValue())),
1505  QueryingAA, DepClassTy::NONE);
1506  else
1507  IsDeadAA = &getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(IRP, QueryingAA, DepClassTy::NONE);
1508 
1509  // Don't use recursive reasoning.
1510  if (QueryingAA == IsDeadAA)
1511  return false;
1512 
1513  if (IsDeadAA->isAssumedDead()) {
1514  if (QueryingAA)
1515  recordDependence(*IsDeadAA, *QueryingAA, DepClass);
1516  if (!IsDeadAA->isKnownDead())
1517  UsedAssumedInformation = true;
1518  return true;
1519  }
1520 
1521  return false;
1522 }

1524 bool Attributor::isAssumedDead(const BasicBlock &BB,
1525  const AbstractAttribute *QueryingAA,
1526  const AAIsDead *FnLivenessAA,
1527  DepClassTy DepClass) {
1528  const Function &F = *BB.getParent();
1529  if (!FnLivenessAA || FnLivenessAA->getAnchorScope() != &F)
1530  FnLivenessAA = &getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(IRPosition::function(F),
1531  QueryingAA, DepClassTy::NONE);
1532 
1533  // Don't use recursive reasoning.
1534  if (QueryingAA == FnLivenessAA)
1535  return false;
1536 
1537  if (FnLivenessAA->isAssumedDead(&BB)) {
1538  if (QueryingAA)
1539  recordDependence(*FnLivenessAA, *QueryingAA, DepClass);
1540  return true;
1541  }
1542 
1543  return false;
1544 }
1545 
1546 bool Attributor::checkForAllUses(
1547  function_ref<bool(const Use &, bool &)> Pred,
1548  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA, const Value &V,
1549  bool CheckBBLivenessOnly, DepClassTy LivenessDepClass,
1550  bool IgnoreDroppableUses,
1551  function_ref<bool(const Use &OldU, const Use &NewU)> EquivalentUseCB) {
1552 
1553  // Check virtual uses first.
1554  for (VirtualUseCallbackTy &CB : VirtualUseCallbacks.lookup(&V))
1555  if (!CB(*this, &QueryingAA))
1556  return false;
1557 
1558  // Check the trivial case first as it catches void values.
1559  if (V.use_empty())
1560  return true;
1561 
1562  const IRPosition &IRP = QueryingAA.getIRPosition();
1563  SmallVector<const Use *, 16> Worklist;
1564  SmallPtrSet<const Use *, 16> Visited;
1565 
1566  auto AddUsers = [&](const Value &V, const Use *OldUse) {
1567  for (const Use &UU : V.uses()) {
1568  if (OldUse && EquivalentUseCB && !EquivalentUseCB(*OldUse, UU)) {
1569  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Potential copy was "
1570  "rejected by the equivalence call back: "
1571  << *UU << "!\n");
1572  return false;
1573  }
1574 
1575  Worklist.push_back(&UU);
1576  }
1577  return true;
1578  };
1579 
1580  AddUsers(V, /* OldUse */ nullptr);
1581 
1582  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Got " << Worklist.size()
1583  << " initial uses to check\n");
1584 
1585  const Function *ScopeFn = IRP.getAnchorScope();
1586  const auto *LivenessAA =
1587  ScopeFn ? &getAAFor<AAIsDead>(QueryingAA, IRPosition::function(*ScopeFn),
1588  DepClassTy::NONE)
1589  : nullptr;
1590 
1591  while (!Worklist.empty()) {
1592  const Use *U = Worklist.pop_back_val();
1593  if (isa<PHINode>(U->getUser()) && !Visited.insert(U).second)
1594  continue;
1595  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE, {
1596  if (auto *Fn = dyn_cast<Function>(U->getUser()))
1597  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Check use: " << **U << " in " << Fn->getName()
1598  << "\n";
1599  else
1600  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Check use: " << **U << " in " << *U->getUser()
1601  << "\n";
1602  });
1603  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
1604  if (isAssumedDead(*U, &QueryingAA, LivenessAA, UsedAssumedInformation,
1605  CheckBBLivenessOnly, LivenessDepClass)) {
1606  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE,
1607  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Dead use, skip!\n");
1608  continue;
1609  }
1610  if (IgnoreDroppableUses && U->getUser()->isDroppable()) {
1611  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE,
1612  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Droppable user, skip!\n");
1613  continue;
1614  }
1615 
1616  if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(U->getUser())) {
1617  if (&SI->getOperandUse(0) == U) {
1618  if (!Visited.insert(U).second)
1619  continue;
1620  SmallSetVector<Value *, 4> PotentialCopies;
1621  if (AA::getPotentialCopiesOfStoredValue(
1622  *this, *SI, PotentialCopies, QueryingAA, UsedAssumedInformation,
1623  /* OnlyExact */ true)) {
1624  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE,
1625  dbgs()
1626  << "[Attributor] Value is stored, continue with "
1627  << PotentialCopies.size()
1628  << " potential copies instead!\n");
1629  for (Value *PotentialCopy : PotentialCopies)
1630  if (!AddUsers(*PotentialCopy, U))
1631  return false;
1632  continue;
1633  }
1634  }
1635  }
1636 
1637  bool Follow = false;
1638  if (!Pred(*U, Follow))
1639  return false;
1640  if (!Follow)
1641  continue;
1642 
1643  User &Usr = *U->getUser();
1644  AddUsers(Usr, /* OldUse */ nullptr);
1645 
1646  auto *RI = dyn_cast<ReturnInst>(&Usr);
1647  if (!RI)
1648  continue;
1649 
1650  Function &F = *RI->getFunction();
1651  auto CallSitePred = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
1652  return AddUsers(*ACS.getInstruction(), U);
1653  };
1654  if (!checkForAllCallSites(CallSitePred, F, /* RequireAllCallSites */ true,
1655  &QueryingAA, UsedAssumedInformation)) {
1656  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Could not follow return instruction "
1657  "to all call sites: "
1658  << *RI << "\n");
1659  return false;
1660  }
1661  }
1662 
1663  return true;
1664 }
1665 
1666 bool Attributor::checkForAllCallSites(function_ref<bool(AbstractCallSite)> Pred,
1667  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA,
1668  bool RequireAllCallSites,
1669  bool &UsedAssumedInformation) {
1670  // We can try to determine information from
1671  // the call sites. However, this is only possible all call sites are known,
1672  // hence the function has internal linkage.
1673  const IRPosition &IRP = QueryingAA.getIRPosition();
1674  const Function *AssociatedFunction = IRP.getAssociatedFunction();
1675  if (!AssociatedFunction) {
1676  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] No function associated with " << IRP
1677  << "\n");
1678  return false;
1679  }
1680 
1681  return checkForAllCallSites(Pred, *AssociatedFunction, RequireAllCallSites,
1682  &QueryingAA, UsedAssumedInformation);
1683 }
1684 
1685 bool Attributor::checkForAllCallSites(function_ref<bool(AbstractCallSite)> Pred,
1686  const Function &Fn,
1687  bool RequireAllCallSites,
1688  const AbstractAttribute *QueryingAA,
1689  bool &UsedAssumedInformation,
1690  bool CheckPotentiallyDead) {
1691  if (RequireAllCallSites && !Fn.hasLocalLinkage()) {
1692  LLVM_DEBUG(
1693  dbgs()
1694  << "[Attributor] Function " << Fn.getName()
1695  << " has no internal linkage, hence not all call sites are known\n");
1696  return false;
1697  }
1698  // Check virtual uses first.
1699  for (VirtualUseCallbackTy &CB : VirtualUseCallbacks.lookup(&Fn))
1700  if (!CB(*this, QueryingAA))
1701  return false;
1702 
1703  SmallVector<const Use *, 8> Uses(make_pointer_range(Fn.uses()));
1704  for (unsigned u = 0; u < Uses.size(); ++u) {
1705  const Use &U = *Uses[u];
1706  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE, {
1707  if (auto *Fn = dyn_cast<Function>(U))
1708  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Check use: " << Fn->getName() << " in "
1709  << *U.getUser() << "\n";
1710  else
1711  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Check use: " << *U << " in " << *U.getUser()
1712  << "\n";
1713  });
1714  if (!CheckPotentiallyDead &&
1715  isAssumedDead(U, QueryingAA, nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation,
1716  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ true)) {
1717  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE,
1718  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Dead use, skip!\n");
1719  continue;
1720  }
1721  if (ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(U.getUser())) {
1722  if (CE->isCast() && CE->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
1723  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE, {
1724  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Use, is constant cast expression, add "
1725  << CE->getNumUses() << " uses of that expression instead!\n";
1726  });
1727  for (const Use &CEU : CE->uses())
1728  Uses.push_back(&CEU);
1729  continue;
1730  }
1731  }
1732 
1733  AbstractCallSite ACS(&U);
1734  if (!ACS) {
1735  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Function " << Fn.getName()
1736  << " has non call site use " << *U.get() << " in "
1737  << *U.getUser() << "\n");
1738  // BlockAddress users are allowed.
1739  if (isa<BlockAddress>(U.getUser()))
1740  continue;
1741  return false;
1742  }
1743 
1744  const Use *EffectiveUse =
1745  ACS.isCallbackCall() ? &ACS.getCalleeUseForCallback() : &U;
1746  if (!ACS.isCallee(EffectiveUse)) {
1747  if (!RequireAllCallSites) {
1748  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] User " << *EffectiveUse->getUser()
1749  << " is not a call of " << Fn.getName()
1750  << ", skip use\n");
1751  continue;
1752  }
1753  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] User " << *EffectiveUse->getUser()
1754  << " is an invalid use of " << Fn.getName() << "\n");
1755  return false;
1756  }
1757 
1758  // Make sure the arguments that can be matched between the call site and the
1759  // callee argee on their type. It is unlikely they do not and it doesn't
1760  // make sense for all attributes to know/care about this.
1761  assert(&Fn == ACS.getCalledFunction() && "Expected known callee");
1762  unsigned MinArgsParams =
1763  std::min(size_t(ACS.getNumArgOperands()), Fn.arg_size());
1764  for (unsigned u = 0; u < MinArgsParams; ++u) {
1765  Value *CSArgOp = ACS.getCallArgOperand(u);
1766  if (CSArgOp && Fn.getArg(u)->getType() != CSArgOp->getType()) {
1767  LLVM_DEBUG(
1768  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Call site / callee argument type mismatch ["
1769  << u << "@" << Fn.getName() << ": "
1770  << *Fn.getArg(u)->getType() << " vs. "
1771  << *ACS.getCallArgOperand(u)->getType() << "\n");
1772  return false;
1773  }
1774  }
1775 
1776  if (Pred(ACS))
1777  continue;
1778 
1779  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Call site callback failed for "
1780  << *ACS.getInstruction() << "\n");
1781  return false;
1782  }
1783 
1784  return true;
1785 }

1791  return EnableCallSiteSpecific;

1839 static bool checkForAllInstructionsImpl(
1840  Attributor *A, InformationCache::OpcodeInstMapTy &OpcodeInstMap,
1841  function_ref<bool(Instruction &)> Pred, const AbstractAttribute *QueryingAA,
1842  const AAIsDead *LivenessAA, const ArrayRef<unsigned> &Opcodes,
1843  bool &UsedAssumedInformation, bool CheckBBLivenessOnly = false,
1844  bool CheckPotentiallyDead = false) {
1845  for (unsigned Opcode : Opcodes) {
1846  // Check if we have instructions with this opcode at all first.
1847  auto *Insts = OpcodeInstMap.lookup(Opcode);
1848  if (!Insts)
1849  continue;
1850 
1851  for (Instruction *I : *Insts) {
1852  // Skip dead instructions.
1853  if (A && !CheckPotentiallyDead &&
1854  A->isAssumedDead(IRPosition::inst(*I), QueryingAA, LivenessAA,
1855  UsedAssumedInformation, CheckBBLivenessOnly)) {
1856  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE,
1857  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Instruction " << *I
1858  << " is potentially dead, skip!\n";);
1859  continue;
1860  }
1861 
1862  if (!Pred(*I))
1863  return false;
1864  }
1865  }
1866  return true;
1867 }

1869 bool Attributor::checkForAllInstructions(function_ref<bool(Instruction &)> Pred,
1870  const Function *Fn,
1871  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA,
1872  const ArrayRef<unsigned> &Opcodes,
1873  bool &UsedAssumedInformation,
1874  bool CheckBBLivenessOnly,
1875  bool CheckPotentiallyDead) {
1876  // Since we need to provide instructions we have to have an exact definition.
1877  if (!Fn || Fn->isDeclaration())
1878  return false;
1879 
1880  // TODO: use the function scope once we have call site AAReturnedValues.
1881  const IRPosition &QueryIRP = IRPosition::function(*Fn);
1882  const auto *LivenessAA =
1883  CheckPotentiallyDead
1884  ? nullptr
1885  : &(getAAFor<AAIsDead>(QueryingAA, QueryIRP, DepClassTy::NONE));
1886 
1887  auto &OpcodeInstMap = InfoCache.getOpcodeInstMapForFunction(*Fn);
1888  if (!checkForAllInstructionsImpl(this, OpcodeInstMap, Pred, &QueryingAA,
1889  LivenessAA, Opcodes, UsedAssumedInformation,
1890  CheckBBLivenessOnly, CheckPotentiallyDead))
1891  return false;
1892 
1893  return true;
1894 }

1901  bool CheckPotentiallyDead) {

1937 void Attributor::runTillFixpoint() {
1938  TimeTraceScope TimeScope("Attributor::runTillFixpoint");
1939  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Identified and initialized "
1940  << DG.SyntheticRoot.Deps.size()
1941  << " abstract attributes.\n");
1942 
1943  // Now that all abstract attributes are collected and initialized we start
1944  // the abstract analysis.
1945 
1946  unsigned IterationCounter = 1;
1947  unsigned MaxIterations =
1948  Configuration.MaxFixpointIterations.value_or(SetFixpointIterations);
1949 
1950  SmallVector<AbstractAttribute *, 32> ChangedAAs;
1951  SetVector<AbstractAttribute *> Worklist, InvalidAAs;
1952  Worklist.insert(DG.SyntheticRoot.begin(), DG.SyntheticRoot.end());
1953 
1954  do {
1955  // Remember the size to determine new attributes.
1956  size_t NumAAs = DG.SyntheticRoot.Deps.size();
1957  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n\n[Attributor] #Iteration: " << IterationCounter
1958  << ", Worklist size: " << Worklist.size() << "\n");
1959 
1960  // For invalid AAs we can fix dependent AAs that have a required dependence,
1961  // thereby folding long dependence chains in a single step without the need
1962  // to run updates.
1963  for (unsigned u = 0; u < InvalidAAs.size(); ++u) {
1964  AbstractAttribute *InvalidAA = InvalidAAs[u];
1965 
1966  // Check the dependences to fast track invalidation.
1967  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE,
1968  dbgs() << "[Attributor] InvalidAA: " << *InvalidAA
1969  << " has " << InvalidAA->Deps.size()
1970  << " required & optional dependences\n");
1971  for (auto &DepIt : InvalidAA->Deps) {
1972  AbstractAttribute *DepAA = cast<AbstractAttribute>(DepIt.getPointer());
1973  if (DepIt.getInt() == unsigned(DepClassTy::OPTIONAL)) {
1974  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE,
1975  dbgs() << " - recompute: " << *DepAA);
1976  Worklist.insert(DepAA);
1977  continue;
1978  }
1979  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(VERBOSE_DEBUG_TYPE, dbgs()
1980  << " - invalidate: " << *DepAA);
1981  DepAA->getState().indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
1982  assert(DepAA->getState().isAtFixpoint() && "Expected fixpoint state!");
1983  if (!DepAA->getState().isValidState())
1984  InvalidAAs.insert(DepAA);
1985  else
1986  ChangedAAs.push_back(DepAA);
1987  }
1988  InvalidAA->Deps.clear();
1989  }
1990 
1991  // Add all abstract attributes that are potentially dependent on one that
1992  // changed to the work list.
1993  for (AbstractAttribute *ChangedAA : ChangedAAs) {
1994  for (auto &DepIt : ChangedAA->Deps)
1995  Worklist.insert(cast<AbstractAttribute>(DepIt.getPointer()));
1996  ChangedAA->Deps.clear();
1997  }
1998 
1999  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] #Iteration: " << IterationCounter
2000  << ", Worklist+Dependent size: " << Worklist.size()
2001  << "\n");
2002 
2003  // Reset the changed and invalid set.
2004  ChangedAAs.clear();
2005  InvalidAAs.clear();
2006 
2007  // Update all abstract attribute in the work list and record the ones that
2008  // changed.
2009  for (AbstractAttribute *AA : Worklist) {
2010  const auto &AAState = AA->getState();
2011  if (!AAState.isAtFixpoint())
2012  if (updateAA(*AA) == ChangeStatus::CHANGED)
2013  ChangedAAs.push_back(AA);
2014 
2015  // Use the InvalidAAs vector to propagate invalid states fast transitively
2016  // without requiring updates.
2017  if (!AAState.isValidState())
2018  InvalidAAs.insert(AA);
2019  }
2020 
2021  // Add attributes to the changed set if they have been created in the last
2022  // iteration.
2023  ChangedAAs.append(DG.SyntheticRoot.begin() + NumAAs,
2024  DG.SyntheticRoot.end());
2025 
2026  // Reset the work list and repopulate with the changed abstract attributes.
2027  // Note that dependent ones are added above.
2028  Worklist.clear();
2029  Worklist.insert(ChangedAAs.begin(), ChangedAAs.end());
2030  Worklist.insert(QueryAAsAwaitingUpdate.begin(),
2031  QueryAAsAwaitingUpdate.end());
2032  QueryAAsAwaitingUpdate.clear();
2033 
2034  } while (!Worklist.empty() &&
2035  (IterationCounter++ < MaxIterations || VerifyMaxFixpointIterations));
2036 
2037  if (IterationCounter > MaxIterations && !Functions.empty()) {
2038  auto Remark = [&](OptimizationRemarkMissed ORM) {
2039  return ORM << "Attributor did not reach a fixpoint after "
2040  << ore::NV("Iterations", MaxIterations) << " iterations.";
2041  };
2042  Function *F = Functions.front();
2043  emitRemark<OptimizationRemarkMissed>(F, "FixedPoint", Remark);
2044  }
2045 
2046  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n[Attributor] Fixpoint iteration done after: "
2047  << IterationCounter << "/" << MaxIterations
2048  << " iterations\n");
2049 
2050  // Reset abstract arguments not settled in a sound fixpoint by now. This
2051  // happens when we stopped the fixpoint iteration early. Note that only the
2052  // ones marked as "changed" *and* the ones transitively depending on them
2053  // need to be reverted to a pessimistic state. Others might not be in a
2054  // fixpoint state but we can use the optimistic results for them anyway.
2055  SmallPtrSet<AbstractAttribute *, 32> Visited;
2056  for (unsigned u = 0; u < ChangedAAs.size(); u++) {
2057  AbstractAttribute *ChangedAA = ChangedAAs[u];
2058  if (!Visited.insert(ChangedAA).second)
2059  continue;
2060 
2061  AbstractState &State = ChangedAA->getState();
2062  if (!State.isAtFixpoint()) {
2063  State.indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
2064 
2065  NumAttributesTimedOut++;
2066  }
2067 
2068  for (auto &DepIt : ChangedAA->Deps)
2069  ChangedAAs.push_back(cast<AbstractAttribute>(DepIt.getPointer()));
2070  ChangedAA->Deps.clear();
2071  }
2072 
2073  LLVM_DEBUG({
2074  if (!Visited.empty())
2075  dbgs() << "\n[Attributor] Finalized " << Visited.size()
2076  << " abstract attributes.\n";
2077  });
2078 
2079  if (VerifyMaxFixpointIterations && IterationCounter != MaxIterations) {
2080  errs() << "\n[Attributor] Fixpoint iteration done after: "
2081  << IterationCounter << "/" << MaxIterations << " iterations\n";
2082  llvm_unreachable("The fixpoint was not reached with exactly the number of "
2083  "specified iterations!");
2084  }
2085 }

2087 void Attributor::registerForUpdate(AbstractAttribute &AA) {

2089  "Non-query AAs should not be required to register for updates!");
2090  QueryAAsAwaitingUpdate.insert(&AA);
2091 }

2093 ChangeStatus Attributor::manifestAttributes() {
2094  TimeTraceScope TimeScope("Attributor::manifestAttributes");
2095  size_t NumFinalAAs = DG.SyntheticRoot.Deps.size();
2096 
2097  unsigned NumManifested = 0;
2098  unsigned NumAtFixpoint = 0;
2099  ChangeStatus ManifestChange = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
2100  for (auto &DepAA : DG.SyntheticRoot.Deps) {
2101  AbstractAttribute *AA = cast<AbstractAttribute>(DepAA.getPointer());
2102  AbstractState &State = AA->getState();
2103 
2104  // If there is not already a fixpoint reached, we can now take the
2105  // optimistic state. This is correct because we enforced a pessimistic one
2106  // on abstract attributes that were transitively dependent on a changed one
2107  // already above.
2108  if (!State.isAtFixpoint())
2109  State.indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
2110 
2111  // We must not manifest Attributes that use Callbase info.
2112  if (AA->hasCallBaseContext())
2113  continue;
2114  // If the state is invalid, we do not try to manifest it.
2115  if (!State.isValidState())
2116  continue;
2117 
2118  if (AA->getCtxI() && !isRunOn(*AA->getAnchorScope()))
2119  continue;
2120 
2121  // Skip dead code.
2122  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
2123  if (isAssumedDead(*AA, nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation,
2124  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ true))
2125  continue;
2126  // Check if the manifest debug counter that allows skipping manifestation of
2127  // AAs
2128  if (!DebugCounter::shouldExecute(ManifestDBGCounter))
2129  continue;
2130  // Manifest the state and record if we changed the IR.
2131  ChangeStatus LocalChange = AA->manifest(*this);
2132  if (LocalChange == ChangeStatus::CHANGED && AreStatisticsEnabled())
2133  AA->trackStatistics();
2134  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Manifest " << LocalChange << " : " << *AA
2135  << "\n");
2136 
2137  ManifestChange = ManifestChange | LocalChange;
2138 
2139  NumAtFixpoint++;
2140  NumManifested += (LocalChange == ChangeStatus::CHANGED);
2141  }
2142 
2143  (void)NumManifested;
2144  (void)NumAtFixpoint;
2145  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n[Attributor] Manifested " << NumManifested
2146  << " arguments while " << NumAtFixpoint
2147  << " were in a valid fixpoint state\n");
2148 
2149  NumAttributesManifested += NumManifested;
2150  NumAttributesValidFixpoint += NumAtFixpoint;
2151 
2152  (void)NumFinalAAs;
2153  if (NumFinalAAs != DG.SyntheticRoot.Deps.size()) {
2154  auto DepIt = DG.SyntheticRoot.Deps.begin();
2155  for (unsigned u = 0; u < NumFinalAAs; ++u)
2156  ++DepIt;
2157  for (unsigned u = NumFinalAAs; u < DG.SyntheticRoot.Deps.size();
2158  ++u, ++DepIt) {
2159  errs() << "Unexpected abstract attribute: "
2160  << cast<AbstractAttribute>(DepIt->getPointer()) << " :: "
2161  << cast<AbstractAttribute>(DepIt->getPointer())
2162  ->getIRPosition()
2163  .getAssociatedValue()
2164  << "\n";
2165  }
2166  llvm_unreachable("Expected the final number of abstract attributes to "
2167  "remain unchanged!");
2168  }
2169  return ManifestChange;
2170 }

2172 void Attributor::identifyDeadInternalFunctions() {
2173  // Early exit if we don't intend to delete functions.
2174  if (!Configuration.DeleteFns)
2175  return;
2176 
2177  // To avoid triggering an assertion in the lazy call graph we will not delete
2178  // any internal library functions. We should modify the assertion though and
2179  // allow internals to be deleted.
2180  const auto *TLI =
2181  isModulePass()
2182  ? nullptr
2183  : getInfoCache().getTargetLibraryInfoForFunction(*Functions.back());
2184  LibFunc LF;
2185 
2186  // Identify dead internal functions and delete them. This happens outside
2187  // the other fixpoint analysis as we might treat potentially dead functions
2188  // as live to lower the number of iterations. If they happen to be dead, the
2189  // below fixpoint loop will identify and eliminate them.
2190 
2191  SmallVector<Function *, 8> InternalFns;
2192  for (Function *F : Functions)
2193  if (F->hasLocalLinkage() && (isModulePass() || !TLI->getLibFunc(*F, LF)))
2194  InternalFns.push_back(F);
2195 
2196  SmallPtrSet<Function *, 8> LiveInternalFns;
2197  bool FoundLiveInternal = true;
2198  while (FoundLiveInternal) {
2199  FoundLiveInternal = false;
2200  for (unsigned u = 0, e = InternalFns.size(); u < e; ++u) {
2201  Function *F = InternalFns[u];
2202  if (!F)
2203  continue;
2204 
2205  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
2206  if (checkForAllCallSites(
2207  [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
2208  Function *Callee = ACS.getInstruction()->getFunction();
2209  return ToBeDeletedFunctions.count(Callee) ||
2210  (Functions.count(Callee) && Callee->hasLocalLinkage() &&
2211  !LiveInternalFns.count(Callee));
2212  },
2213  *F, true, nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation)) {
2214  continue;
2215  }
2216 
2217  LiveInternalFns.insert(F);
2218  InternalFns[u] = nullptr;
2219  FoundLiveInternal = true;
2220  }
2221  }
2222 
2223  for (unsigned u = 0, e = InternalFns.size(); u < e; ++u)
2224  if (Function *F = InternalFns[u])
2225  ToBeDeletedFunctions.insert(F);
2226 }

2228 ChangeStatus Attributor::cleanupIR() {
2229  TimeTraceScope TimeScope("Attributor::cleanupIR");
2230  // Delete stuff at the end to avoid invalid references and a nice order.
2231  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n[Attributor] Delete/replace at least "
2232  << ToBeDeletedFunctions.size() << " functions and "
2233  << ToBeDeletedBlocks.size() << " blocks and "
2234  << ToBeDeletedInsts.size() << " instructions and "
2235  << ToBeChangedValues.size() << " values and "
2236  << ToBeChangedUses.size() << " uses. To insert "
2237  << ToBeChangedToUnreachableInsts.size()
2238  << " unreachables.\n"
2239  << "Preserve manifest added " << ManifestAddedBlocks.size()
2240  << " blocks\n");
2241 
2242  SmallVector<WeakTrackingVH, 32> DeadInsts;
2243  SmallVector<Instruction *, 32> TerminatorsToFold;
2244 
2245  auto ReplaceUse = [&](Use *U, Value *NewV) {
2246  Value *OldV = U->get();
2247 
2248  // If we plan to replace NewV we need to update it at this point.
2249  do {
2250  const auto &Entry = ToBeChangedValues.lookup(NewV);
2251  if (!get<0>(Entry))
2252  break;
2253  NewV = get<0>(Entry);
2254  } while (true);
2255 
2256  Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U->getUser());
2257  assert((!I || isRunOn(*I->getFunction())) &&
2258  "Cannot replace an instruction outside the current SCC!");
2259 
2260  // Do not replace uses in returns if the value is a must-tail call we will
2261  // not delete.
2262  if (auto *RI = dyn_cast_or_null<ReturnInst>(I)) {
2263  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(OldV->stripPointerCasts()))
2264  if (CI->isMustTailCall() && !ToBeDeletedInsts.count(CI))
2265  return;
2266  // If we rewrite a return and the new value is not an argument, strip the
2267  // `returned` attribute as it is wrong now.
2268  if (!isa<Argument>(NewV))
2269  for (auto &Arg : RI->getFunction()->args())
2270  Arg.removeAttr(Attribute::Returned);
2271  }
2272 
2273  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Use " << *NewV << " in " << *U->getUser()
2274  << " instead of " << *OldV << "\n");
2275  U->set(NewV);
2276 
2277  if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(OldV)) {
2278  CGModifiedFunctions.insert(I->getFunction());
2279  if (!isa<PHINode>(I) && !ToBeDeletedInsts.count(I) &&
2280  isInstructionTriviallyDead(I))
2281  DeadInsts.push_back(I);
2282  }
2283  if (isa<UndefValue>(NewV) && isa<CallBase>(U->getUser())) {
2284  auto *CB = cast<CallBase>(U->getUser());
2285  if (CB->isArgOperand(U)) {
2286  unsigned Idx = CB->getArgOperandNo(U);
2287  CB->removeParamAttr(Idx, Attribute::NoUndef);
2288  Function *Fn = CB->getCalledFunction();
2289  if (Fn && Fn->arg_size() > Idx)
2290  Fn->removeParamAttr(Idx, Attribute::NoUndef);
2291  }
2292  }
2293  if (isa<Constant>(NewV) && isa<BranchInst>(U->getUser())) {
2294  Instruction *UserI = cast<Instruction>(U->getUser());
2295  if (isa<UndefValue>(NewV)) {
2296  ToBeChangedToUnreachableInsts.insert(UserI);
2297  } else {
2298  TerminatorsToFold.push_back(UserI);
2299  }
2300  }
2301  };
2302 
2303  for (auto &It : ToBeChangedUses) {
2304  Use *U = It.first;
2305  Value *NewV = It.second;
2306  ReplaceUse(U, NewV);
2307  }
2308 
2309  SmallVector<Use *, 4> Uses;
2310  for (auto &It : ToBeChangedValues) {
2311  Value *OldV = It.first;
2312  auto [NewV, Done] = It.second;
2313  Uses.clear();
2314  for (auto &U : OldV->uses())
2315  if (Done || !U.getUser()->isDroppable())
2316  Uses.push_back(&U);
2317  for (Use *U : Uses) {
2318  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U->getUser()))
2319  if (!isRunOn(*I->getFunction()))
2320  continue;
2321  ReplaceUse(U, NewV);
2322  }
2323  }
2324 
2325  for (const auto &V : InvokeWithDeadSuccessor)
2326  if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast_or_null<InvokeInst>(V)) {
2327  assert(isRunOn(*II->getFunction()) &&
2328  "Cannot replace an invoke outside the current SCC!");
2329  bool UnwindBBIsDead = II->hasFnAttr(Attribute::NoUnwind);
2330  bool NormalBBIsDead = II->hasFnAttr(Attribute::NoReturn);
2331  bool Invoke2CallAllowed =
2332  !AAIsDead::mayCatchAsynchronousExceptions(*II->getFunction());
2333  assert((UnwindBBIsDead || NormalBBIsDead) &&
2334  "Invoke does not have dead successors!");
2335  BasicBlock *BB = II->getParent();
2336  BasicBlock *NormalDestBB = II->getNormalDest();
2337  if (UnwindBBIsDead) {
2338  Instruction *NormalNextIP = &NormalDestBB->front();
2339  if (Invoke2CallAllowed) {
2340  changeToCall(II);
2341  NormalNextIP = BB->getTerminator();
2342  }
2343  if (NormalBBIsDead)
2344  ToBeChangedToUnreachableInsts.insert(NormalNextIP);
2345  } else {
2346  assert(NormalBBIsDead && "Broken invariant!");
2347  if (!NormalDestBB->getUniquePredecessor())
2348  NormalDestBB = SplitBlockPredecessors(NormalDestBB, {BB}, ".dead");
2349  ToBeChangedToUnreachableInsts.insert(&NormalDestBB->front());
2350  }
2351  }
2352  for (Instruction *I : TerminatorsToFold) {
2353  assert(isRunOn(*I->getFunction()) &&
2354  "Cannot replace a terminator outside the current SCC!");
2355  CGModifiedFunctions.insert(I->getFunction());
2356  ConstantFoldTerminator(I->getParent());
2357  }
2358  for (const auto &V : ToBeChangedToUnreachableInsts)
2359  if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast_or_null<Instruction>(V)) {
2360  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Change to unreachable: " << *I
2361  << "\n");
2362  assert(isRunOn(*I->getFunction()) &&
2363  "Cannot replace an instruction outside the current SCC!");
2364  CGModifiedFunctions.insert(I->getFunction());
2365  changeToUnreachable(I);
2366  }
2367 
2368  for (const auto &V : ToBeDeletedInsts) {
2369  if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast_or_null<Instruction>(V)) {
2370  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(I)) {
2371  assert((isa<IntrinsicInst>(CB) || isRunOn(*I->getFunction())) &&
2372  "Cannot delete an instruction outside the current SCC!");
2373  if (!isa<IntrinsicInst>(CB))
2374  Configuration.CGUpdater.removeCallSite(*CB);
2375  }
2376  I->dropDroppableUses();
2377  CGModifiedFunctions.insert(I->getFunction());
2378  if (!I->getType()->isVoidTy())
2379  I->replaceAllUsesWith(UndefValue::get(I->getType()));
2380  if (!isa<PHINode>(I) && isInstructionTriviallyDead(I))
2381  DeadInsts.push_back(I);
2382  else
2383  I->eraseFromParent();
2384  }
2385  }
2386 
2387  llvm::erase_if(DeadInsts, [&](WeakTrackingVH I) { return !I; });
2388 
2389  LLVM_DEBUG({
2390  dbgs() << "[Attributor] DeadInsts size: " << DeadInsts.size() << "\n";
2391  for (auto &I : DeadInsts)
2392  if (I)
2393  dbgs() << " - " << *I << "\n";
2394  });
2395 
2396  RecursivelyDeleteTriviallyDeadInstructions(DeadInsts);
2397 
2398  if (unsigned NumDeadBlocks = ToBeDeletedBlocks.size()) {
2399  SmallVector<BasicBlock *, 8> ToBeDeletedBBs;
2400  ToBeDeletedBBs.reserve(NumDeadBlocks);
2401  for (BasicBlock *BB : ToBeDeletedBlocks) {
2402  assert(isRunOn(*BB->getParent()) &&
2403  "Cannot delete a block outside the current SCC!");
2404  CGModifiedFunctions.insert(BB->getParent());
2405  // Do not delete BBs added during manifests of AAs.
2406  if (ManifestAddedBlocks.contains(BB))
2407  continue;
2408  ToBeDeletedBBs.push_back(BB);
2409  }
2410  // Actually we do not delete the blocks but squash them into a single
2411  // unreachable but untangling branches that jump here is something we need
2412  // to do in a more generic way.
2413  detachDeadBlocks(ToBeDeletedBBs, nullptr);
2414  }
2415 
2416  identifyDeadInternalFunctions();
2417 
2418  // Rewrite the functions as requested during manifest.
2419  ChangeStatus ManifestChange = rewriteFunctionSignatures(CGModifiedFunctions);
2420 
2421  for (Function *Fn : CGModifiedFunctions)
2422  if (!ToBeDeletedFunctions.count(Fn) && Functions.count(Fn))
2423  Configuration.CGUpdater.reanalyzeFunction(*Fn);
2424 
2425  for (Function *Fn : ToBeDeletedFunctions) {
2426  if (!Functions.count(Fn))
2427  continue;
2428  Configuration.CGUpdater.removeFunction(*Fn);
2429  }
2430 
2431  if (!ToBeChangedUses.empty())
2432  ManifestChange = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
2433 
2434  if (!ToBeChangedToUnreachableInsts.empty())
2435  ManifestChange = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
2436 
2437  if (!ToBeDeletedFunctions.empty())
2438  ManifestChange = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
2439 
2440  if (!ToBeDeletedBlocks.empty())
2441  ManifestChange = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
2442 
2443  if (!ToBeDeletedInsts.empty())
2444  ManifestChange = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
2445 
2446  if (!InvokeWithDeadSuccessor.empty())
2447  ManifestChange = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
2448 
2449  if (!DeadInsts.empty())
2450  ManifestChange = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
2451 
2452  NumFnDeleted += ToBeDeletedFunctions.size();
2453 
2454  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Deleted " << ToBeDeletedFunctions.size()
2455  << " functions after manifest.\n");
2456 
2457 #ifdef EXPENSIVE_CHECKS
2458  for (Function *F : Functions) {
2459  if (ToBeDeletedFunctions.count(F))
2460  continue;
2461  assert(!verifyFunction(*F, &errs()) && "Module verification failed!");
2462  }
2463 #endif
2464 
2465  return ManifestChange;
2466 }

2468 ChangeStatus Attributor::run() {
2469  TimeTraceScope TimeScope("Attributor::run");
2470  AttributorCallGraph ACallGraph(*this);
2471 
2472  if (PrintCallGraph)
2473  ACallGraph.populateAll();
2474 
2475  Phase = AttributorPhase::UPDATE;
2476  runTillFixpoint();
2477 
2478  // dump graphs on demand
2479  if (DumpDepGraph)
2480  DG.dumpGraph();
2481 
2482  if (ViewDepGraph)
2483  DG.viewGraph();
2484 
2485  if (PrintDependencies)
2486  DG.print();
2487 
2488  Phase = AttributorPhase::MANIFEST;
2489  ChangeStatus ManifestChange = manifestAttributes();
2490 
2491  Phase = AttributorPhase::CLEANUP;

2493

2498 }
