2500 ChangeStatus Attributor::updateAA(AbstractAttribute &AA) {
2501  TimeTraceScope TimeScope("updateAA", [&]() {
2502  return AA.getName() + std::to_string(AA.getIRPosition().getPositionKind());
2503  });
2504  assert(Phase == AttributorPhase::UPDATE &&
2505  "We can update AA only in the update stage!");
2506 
2507  // Use a new dependence vector for this update.
2508  DependenceVector DV;
2509  DependenceStack.push_back(&DV);
2510 
2511  auto &AAState = AA.getState();
2512  ChangeStatus CS = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
2513  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
2514  if (!isAssumedDead(AA, nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation,
2515  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ true))
2516  CS = AA.update(*this);
2517 
2518  if (!AA.isQueryAA() && DV.empty() && !AA.getState().isAtFixpoint()) {
2519  // If the AA did not rely on outside information but changed, we run it
2520  // again to see if it found a fixpoint. Most AAs do but we don't require
2521  // them to. Hence, it might take the AA multiple iterations to get to a
2522  // fixpoint even if it does not rely on outside information, which is fine.
2523  ChangeStatus RerunCS = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
2524  if (CS == ChangeStatus::CHANGED)
2525  RerunCS = AA.update(*this);
2526 
2527  // If the attribute did not change during the run or rerun, and it still did
2528  // not query any non-fix information, the state will not change and we can
2529  // indicate that right at this point.
2530  if (RerunCS == ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED && !AA.isQueryAA() && DV.empty())
2531  AAState.indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
2532  }
2533 
2534  if (!AAState.isAtFixpoint())
2535  rememberDependences();
2536 
2537  // Verify the stack was used properly, that is we pop the dependence vector we
2538  // put there earlier.
2539  DependenceVector *PoppedDV = DependenceStack.pop_back_val();
2540  (void)PoppedDV;
2541  assert(PoppedDV == &DV && "Inconsistent usage of the dependence stack!");
2542 
2543  return CS;
2544 }

2546 void Attributor::createShallowWrapper(Function &F) {
2547  assert(!F.isDeclaration() && "Cannot create a wrapper around a declaration!");
2548 
2549  Module &M = *F.getParent();
2550  LLVMContext &Ctx = M.getContext();
2551  FunctionType *FnTy = F.getFunctionType();
2552 
2553  Function *Wrapper =
2554  Function::Create(FnTy, F.getLinkage(), F.getAddressSpace(), F.getName());
2555  F.setName(""); // set the inside function anonymous
2556  M.getFunctionList().insert(F.getIterator(), Wrapper);
2557 
2558  F.setLinkage(GlobalValue::InternalLinkage);
2559 
2560  F.replaceAllUsesWith(Wrapper);
2561  assert(F.use_empty() && "Uses remained after wrapper was created!");
2562 
2563  // Move the COMDAT section to the wrapper.
2564  // TODO: Check if we need to keep it for F as well.
2565  Wrapper->setComdat(F.getComdat());
2566  F.setComdat(nullptr);
2567 
2568  // Copy all metadata and attributes but keep them on F as well.
2569  SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>, 1> MDs;
2570  F.getAllMetadata(MDs);
2571  for (auto MDIt : MDs)
2572  Wrapper->addMetadata(MDIt.first, *MDIt.second);
2573  Wrapper->setAttributes(F.getAttributes());
2574 
2575  // Create the call in the wrapper.
2576  BasicBlock *EntryBB = BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "entry", Wrapper);
2577 
2578  SmallVector<Value *, 8> Args;
2579  Argument *FArgIt = F.arg_begin();
2580  for (Argument &Arg : Wrapper->args()) {
2581  Args.push_back(&Arg);
2582  Arg.setName((FArgIt++)->getName());
2583  }
2584 
2585  CallInst *CI = CallInst::Create(&F, Args, "", EntryBB);
2586  CI->setTailCall(true);
2587  CI->addFnAttr(Attribute::NoInline);
2588  ReturnInst::Create(Ctx, CI->getType()->isVoidTy() ? nullptr : CI, EntryBB);
2589 
2590  NumFnShallowWrappersCreated++;
2591 }

2613 bool Attributor::internalizeFunctions(SmallPtrSetImpl<Function *> &FnSet,
2614  DenseMap<Function *, Function *> &FnMap) {
2615  for (Function *F : FnSet)
2616  if (!Attributor::isInternalizable(*F))
2617  return false;
2618 
2619  FnMap.clear();
2620  // Generate the internalized version of each function.
2621  for (Function *F : FnSet) {
2622  Module &M = *F->getParent();
2623  FunctionType *FnTy = F->getFunctionType();
2624 
2625  // Create a copy of the current function
2626  Function *Copied =
2627  Function::Create(FnTy, F->getLinkage(), F->getAddressSpace(),
2628  F->getName() + ".internalized");
2629  ValueToValueMapTy VMap;
2630  auto *NewFArgIt = Copied->arg_begin();
2631  for (auto &Arg : F->args()) {
2632  auto ArgName = Arg.getName();
2633  NewFArgIt->setName(ArgName);
2634  VMap[&Arg] = &(*NewFArgIt++);
2635  }
2636  SmallVector<ReturnInst *, 8> Returns;
2637 
2638  // Copy the body of the original function to the new one
2639  CloneFunctionInto(Copied, F, VMap,
2640  CloneFunctionChangeType::LocalChangesOnly, Returns);
2641 
2642  // Set the linakage and visibility late as CloneFunctionInto has some
2643  // implicit requirements.
2644  Copied->setVisibility(GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility);
2645  Copied->setLinkage(GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage);
2646 
2647  // Copy metadata
2648  SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>, 1> MDs;
2649  F->getAllMetadata(MDs);
2650  for (auto MDIt : MDs)
2651  if (!Copied->hasMetadata())
2652  Copied->addMetadata(MDIt.first, *MDIt.second);
2653 
2654  M.getFunctionList().insert(F->getIterator(), Copied);
2655  Copied->setDSOLocal(true);
2656  FnMap[F] = Copied;
2657  }
2658 
2659  // Replace all uses of the old function with the new internalized function
2660  // unless the caller is a function that was just internalized.
2661  for (Function *F : FnSet) {
2662  auto &InternalizedFn = FnMap[F];
2663  auto IsNotInternalized = [&](Use &U) -> bool {
2664  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(U.getUser()))
2665  return !FnMap.lookup(CB->getCaller());
2666  return false;
2667  };
2668  F->replaceUsesWithIf(InternalizedFn, IsNotInternalized);
2669  }
2670 
2671  return true;
2672 }

2674 bool Attributor::isValidFunctionSignatureRewrite(
2675  Argument &Arg, ArrayRef<Type *> ReplacementTypes) {
2676 
2677  if (!Configuration.RewriteSignatures)
2678  return false;
2679 
2680  Function *Fn = Arg.getParent();
2681  auto CallSiteCanBeChanged = [Fn](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
2682  // Forbid the call site to cast the function return type. If we need to
2683  // rewrite these functions we need to re-create a cast for the new call site
2684  // (if the old had uses).
2685  if (!ACS.getCalledFunction() ||
2686  ACS.getInstruction()->getType() !=
2687  ACS.getCalledFunction()->getReturnType())
2688  return false;
2689  if (ACS.getCalledOperand()->getType() != Fn->getType())
2690  return false;
2691  // Forbid must-tail calls for now.
2692  return !ACS.isCallbackCall() && !ACS.getInstruction()->isMustTailCall();
2693  };
2694 
2695  // Avoid var-arg functions for now.
2696  if (Fn->isVarArg()) {
2697  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Cannot rewrite var-args functions\n");
2698  return false;
2699  }
2700 
2701  // Avoid functions with complicated argument passing semantics.
2702  AttributeList FnAttributeList = Fn->getAttributes();
2703  if (FnAttributeList.hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::Nest) ||
2704  FnAttributeList.hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::StructRet) ||
2705  FnAttributeList.hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::InAlloca) ||
2706  FnAttributeList.hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::Preallocated)) {
2707  LLVM_DEBUG(
2708  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Cannot rewrite due to complex attribute\n");
2709  return false;
2710  }
2711 
2712  // Avoid callbacks for now.
2713  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
2714  if (!checkForAllCallSites(CallSiteCanBeChanged, *Fn, true, nullptr,
2715  UsedAssumedInformation)) {
2716  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Cannot rewrite all call sites\n");
2717  return false;
2718  }
2719 
2720  auto InstPred = [](Instruction &I) {
2721  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I))
2722  return !CI->isMustTailCall();
2723  return true;
2724  };
2725 
2726  // Forbid must-tail calls for now.
2727  // TODO:
2728  auto &OpcodeInstMap = InfoCache.getOpcodeInstMapForFunction(*Fn);
2729  if (!checkForAllInstructionsImpl(nullptr, OpcodeInstMap, InstPred, nullptr,
2730  nullptr, {Instruction::Call},
2731  UsedAssumedInformation)) {
2732  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Cannot rewrite due to instructions\n");
2733  return false;
2734  }
2735 
2736  return true;
2737 }

2739 bool Attributor::registerFunctionSignatureRewrite(
2740  Argument &Arg, ArrayRef<Type *> ReplacementTypes,
2741  ArgumentReplacementInfo::CalleeRepairCBTy &&CalleeRepairCB,
2742  ArgumentReplacementInfo::ACSRepairCBTy &&ACSRepairCB) {
2743  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Register new rewrite of " << Arg << " in "
2744  << Arg.getParent()->getName() << " with "
2745  << ReplacementTypes.size() << " replacements\n");
2746  assert(isValidFunctionSignatureRewrite(Arg, ReplacementTypes) &&
2747  "Cannot register an invalid rewrite");
2748 
2749  Function *Fn = Arg.getParent();
2750  SmallVectorImpl<std::unique_ptr<ArgumentReplacementInfo>> &ARIs =
2751  ArgumentReplacementMap[Fn];
2752  if (ARIs.empty())
2753  ARIs.resize(Fn->arg_size());
2754 
2755  // If we have a replacement already with less than or equal new arguments,
2756  // ignore this request.
2757  std::unique_ptr<ArgumentReplacementInfo> &ARI = ARIs[Arg.getArgNo()];
2758  if (ARI && ARI->getNumReplacementArgs() <= ReplacementTypes.size()) {
2759  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Existing rewrite is preferred\n");
2760  return false;
2761  }
2762 
2763  // If we have a replacement already but we like the new one better, delete
2764  // the old.
2765  ARI.reset();
2766 
2767  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Register new rewrite of " << Arg << " in "
2768  << Arg.getParent()->getName() << " with "
2769  << ReplacementTypes.size() << " replacements\n");
2770 
2771  // Remember the replacement.
2772  ARI.reset(new ArgumentReplacementInfo(*this, Arg, ReplacementTypes,
2773  std::move(CalleeRepairCB),
2774  std::move(ACSRepairCB)));
2775 
2776  return true;
2777 }

2791 ChangeStatus Attributor::rewriteFunctionSignatures(
2792  SmallSetVector<Function *, 8> &ModifiedFns) {
2793  ChangeStatus Changed = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
2794 
2795  for (auto &It : ArgumentReplacementMap) {
2796  Function *OldFn = It.getFirst();
2797 
2798  // Deleted functions do not require rewrites.
2799  if (!Functions.count(OldFn) || ToBeDeletedFunctions.count(OldFn))
2800  continue;
2801 
2802  const SmallVectorImpl<std::unique_ptr<ArgumentReplacementInfo>> &ARIs =
2803  It.getSecond();
2804  assert(ARIs.size() == OldFn->arg_size() && "Inconsistent state!");
2805 
2806  SmallVector<Type *, 16> NewArgumentTypes;
2807  SmallVector<AttributeSet, 16> NewArgumentAttributes;
2808 
2809  // Collect replacement argument types and copy over existing attributes.
2810  AttributeList OldFnAttributeList = OldFn->getAttributes();
2811  for (Argument &Arg : OldFn->args()) {
2812  if (const std::unique_ptr<ArgumentReplacementInfo> &ARI =
2813  ARIs[Arg.getArgNo()]) {
2814  NewArgumentTypes.append(ARI->ReplacementTypes.begin(),
2815  ARI->ReplacementTypes.end());
2816  NewArgumentAttributes.append(ARI->getNumReplacementArgs(),
2817  AttributeSet());
2818  } else {
2819  NewArgumentTypes.push_back(Arg.getType());
2820  NewArgumentAttributes.push_back(
2821  OldFnAttributeList.getParamAttrs(Arg.getArgNo()));
2822  }
2823  }
2824 
2825  uint64_t LargestVectorWidth = 0;
2826  for (auto *I : NewArgumentTypes)
2827  if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(I))
2828  LargestVectorWidth =
2829  std::max(LargestVectorWidth,
2830  VT->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue());
2831 
2832  FunctionType *OldFnTy = OldFn->getFunctionType();
2833  Type *RetTy = OldFnTy->getReturnType();
2834 
2835  // Construct the new function type using the new arguments types.
2836  FunctionType *NewFnTy =
2837  FunctionType::get(RetTy, NewArgumentTypes, OldFnTy->isVarArg());
2838 
2839  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Function rewrite '" << OldFn->getName()
2840  << "' from " << *OldFn->getFunctionType() << " to "
2841  << *NewFnTy << "\n");
2842 
2843  // Create the new function body and insert it into the module.
2844  Function *NewFn = Function::Create(NewFnTy, OldFn->getLinkage(),
2845  OldFn->getAddressSpace(), "");
2846  Functions.insert(NewFn);
2847  OldFn->getParent()->getFunctionList().insert(OldFn->getIterator(), NewFn);
2848  NewFn->takeName(OldFn);
2849  NewFn->copyAttributesFrom(OldFn);
2850 
2851  // Patch the pointer to LLVM function in debug info descriptor.
2852  NewFn->setSubprogram(OldFn->getSubprogram());
2853  OldFn->setSubprogram(nullptr);
2854 
2855  // Recompute the parameter attributes list based on the new arguments for
2856  // the function.
2857  LLVMContext &Ctx = OldFn->getContext();
2858  NewFn->setAttributes(AttributeList::get(
2859  Ctx, OldFnAttributeList.getFnAttrs(), OldFnAttributeList.getRetAttrs(),
2860  NewArgumentAttributes));
2861  AttributeFuncs::updateMinLegalVectorWidthAttr(*NewFn, LargestVectorWidth);
2862 
2863  // Since we have now created the new function, splice the body of the old
2864  // function right into the new function, leaving the old rotting hulk of the
2865  // function empty.
2866  NewFn->splice(NewFn->begin(), OldFn);
2867 
2868  // Fixup block addresses to reference new function.
2869  SmallVector<BlockAddress *, 8u> BlockAddresses;
2870  for (User *U : OldFn->users())
2871  if (auto *BA = dyn_cast<BlockAddress>(U))
2872  BlockAddresses.push_back(BA);
2873  for (auto *BA : BlockAddresses)
2874  BA->replaceAllUsesWith(BlockAddress::get(NewFn, BA->getBasicBlock()));
2875 
2876  // Set of all "call-like" instructions that invoke the old function mapped
2877  // to their new replacements.
2878  SmallVector<std::pair<CallBase *, CallBase *>, 8> CallSitePairs;
2879 
2880  // Callback to create a new "call-like" instruction for a given one.
2881  auto CallSiteReplacementCreator = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
2882  CallBase *OldCB = cast<CallBase>(ACS.getInstruction());
2883  const AttributeList &OldCallAttributeList = OldCB->getAttributes();
2884 
2885  // Collect the new argument operands for the replacement call site.
2886  SmallVector<Value *, 16> NewArgOperands;
2887  SmallVector<AttributeSet, 16> NewArgOperandAttributes;
2888  for (unsigned OldArgNum = 0; OldArgNum < ARIs.size(); ++OldArgNum) {
2889  unsigned NewFirstArgNum = NewArgOperands.size();
2890  (void)NewFirstArgNum; // only used inside assert.
2891  if (const std::unique_ptr<ArgumentReplacementInfo> &ARI =
2892  ARIs[OldArgNum]) {
2893  if (ARI->ACSRepairCB)
2894  ARI->ACSRepairCB(*ARI, ACS, NewArgOperands);
2895  assert(ARI->getNumReplacementArgs() + NewFirstArgNum ==
2896  NewArgOperands.size() &&
2897  "ACS repair callback did not provide as many operand as new "
2898  "types were registered!");
2899  // TODO: Exose the attribute set to the ACS repair callback
2900  NewArgOperandAttributes.append(ARI->ReplacementTypes.size(),
2901  AttributeSet());
2902  } else {
2903  NewArgOperands.push_back(ACS.getCallArgOperand(OldArgNum));
2904  NewArgOperandAttributes.push_back(
2905  OldCallAttributeList.getParamAttrs(OldArgNum));
2906  }
2907  }
2908 
2909  assert(NewArgOperands.size() == NewArgOperandAttributes.size() &&
2910  "Mismatch # argument operands vs. # argument operand attributes!");
2911  assert(NewArgOperands.size() == NewFn->arg_size() &&
2912  "Mismatch # argument operands vs. # function arguments!");
2913 
2914  SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 4> OperandBundleDefs;
2915  OldCB->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OperandBundleDefs);
2916 
2917  // Create a new call or invoke instruction to replace the old one.
2918  CallBase *NewCB;
2919  if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(OldCB)) {
2920  NewCB =
2921  InvokeInst::Create(NewFn, II->getNormalDest(), II->getUnwindDest(),
2922  NewArgOperands, OperandBundleDefs, "", OldCB);
2923  } else {
2924  auto *NewCI = CallInst::Create(NewFn, NewArgOperands, OperandBundleDefs,
2925  "", OldCB);
2926  NewCI->setTailCallKind(cast<CallInst>(OldCB)->getTailCallKind());
2927  NewCB = NewCI;
2928  }
2929 
2930  // Copy over various properties and the new attributes.
2931  NewCB->copyMetadata(*OldCB, {LLVMContext::MD_prof, LLVMContext::MD_dbg});
2932  NewCB->setCallingConv(OldCB->getCallingConv());
2933  NewCB->takeName(OldCB);
2934  NewCB->setAttributes(AttributeList::get(
2935  Ctx, OldCallAttributeList.getFnAttrs(),
2936  OldCallAttributeList.getRetAttrs(), NewArgOperandAttributes));
2937 
2938  AttributeFuncs::updateMinLegalVectorWidthAttr(*NewCB->getCaller(),
2939  LargestVectorWidth);
2940 
2941  CallSitePairs.push_back({OldCB, NewCB});
2942  return true;
2943  };
2944 
2945  // Use the CallSiteReplacementCreator to create replacement call sites.
2946  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
2947  bool Success = checkForAllCallSites(CallSiteReplacementCreator, *OldFn,
2948  true, nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation,
2949  /* CheckPotentiallyDead */ true);
2950  (void)Success;
2951  assert(Success && "Assumed call site replacement to succeed!");
2952 
2953  // Rewire the arguments.
2954  Argument *OldFnArgIt = OldFn->arg_begin();
2955  Argument *NewFnArgIt = NewFn->arg_begin();
2956  for (unsigned OldArgNum = 0; OldArgNum < ARIs.size();
2957  ++OldArgNum, ++OldFnArgIt) {
2958  if (const std::unique_ptr<ArgumentReplacementInfo> &ARI =
2959  ARIs[OldArgNum]) {
2960  if (ARI->CalleeRepairCB)
2961  ARI->CalleeRepairCB(*ARI, *NewFn, NewFnArgIt);
2962  if (ARI->ReplacementTypes.empty())
2963  OldFnArgIt->replaceAllUsesWith(
2964  PoisonValue::get(OldFnArgIt->getType()));
2965  NewFnArgIt += ARI->ReplacementTypes.size();
2966  } else {
2967  NewFnArgIt->takeName(&*OldFnArgIt);
2968  OldFnArgIt->replaceAllUsesWith(&*NewFnArgIt);
2969  ++NewFnArgIt;
2970  }
2971  }
2972 
2973  // Eliminate the instructions *after* we visited all of them.
2974  for (auto &CallSitePair : CallSitePairs) {
2975  CallBase &OldCB = *CallSitePair.first;
2976  CallBase &NewCB = *CallSitePair.second;
2977  assert(OldCB.getType() == NewCB.getType() &&
2978  "Cannot handle call sites with different types!");
2979  ModifiedFns.insert(OldCB.getFunction());
2980  Configuration.CGUpdater.replaceCallSite(OldCB, NewCB);
2981  OldCB.replaceAllUsesWith(&NewCB);
2982  OldCB.eraseFromParent();
2983  }
2984 
2985  // Replace the function in the call graph (if any).
2986  Configuration.CGUpdater.replaceFunctionWith(*OldFn, *NewFn);
2987 
2988  // If the old function was modified and needed to be reanalyzed, the new one
2989  // does now.
2990  if (ModifiedFns.remove(OldFn))
2991  ModifiedFns.insert(NewFn);
2992 
2993  Changed = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
2994  }
2995 
2996  return Changed;
2997 }

2999 void InformationCache::initializeInformationCache(const Function &CF,
3000  FunctionInfo &FI) {
3001  // As we do not modify the function here we can remove the const
3002  // withouth breaking implicit assumptions. At the end of the day, we could
3003  // initialize the cache eagerly which would look the same to the users.
3004  Function &F = const_cast<Function &>(CF);
3005 
3006  // Walk all instructions to find interesting instructions that might be
3007  // queried by abstract attributes during their initialization or update.
3008  // This has to happen before we create attributes.
3009 
3010  DenseMap<const Value *, std::optional<short>> AssumeUsesMap;
3011 
3012  // Add \p V to the assume uses map which track the number of uses outside of
3013  // "visited" assumes. If no outside uses are left the value is added to the
3014  // assume only use vector.
3015  auto AddToAssumeUsesMap = [&](const Value &V) -> void {
3016  SmallVector<const Instruction *> Worklist;
3017  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&V))
3018  Worklist.push_back(I);
3019  while (!Worklist.empty()) {
3020  const Instruction *I = Worklist.pop_back_val();
3021  std::optional<short> &NumUses = AssumeUsesMap[I];
3022  if (!NumUses)
3023  NumUses = I->getNumUses();
3024  NumUses = *NumUses - /* this assume */ 1;
3025  if (*NumUses != 0)
3026  continue;
3027  AssumeOnlyValues.insert(I);
3028  for (const Value *Op : I->operands())
3029  if (auto *OpI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Op))
3030  Worklist.push_back(OpI);
3031  }
3032  };
3033 
3034  for (Instruction &I : instructions(&F)) {
3035  bool IsInterestingOpcode = false;
3036 
3037  // To allow easy access to all instructions in a function with a given
3038  // opcode we store them in the InfoCache. As not all opcodes are interesting
3039  // to concrete attributes we only cache the ones that are as identified in
3040  // the following switch.
3041  // Note: There are no concrete attributes now so this is initially empty.
3042  switch (I.getOpcode()) {
3043  default:
3044  assert(!isa<CallBase>(&I) &&
3045  "New call base instruction type needs to be known in the "
3046  "Attributor.");
3047  break;
3048  case Instruction::Call:
3049  // Calls are interesting on their own, additionally:
3050  // For `llvm.assume` calls we also fill the KnowledgeMap as we find them.
3051  // For `must-tail` calls we remember the caller and callee.
3052  if (auto *Assume = dyn_cast<AssumeInst>(&I)) {
3053  AssumeOnlyValues.insert(Assume);
3054  fillMapFromAssume(*Assume, KnowledgeMap);
3055  AddToAssumeUsesMap(*Assume->getArgOperand(0));
3056  } else if (cast<CallInst>(I).isMustTailCall()) {
3057  FI.ContainsMustTailCall = true;
3058  if (const Function *Callee = cast<CallInst>(I).getCalledFunction())
3059  getFunctionInfo(*Callee).CalledViaMustTail = true;
3060  }
3061  [[fallthrough]];
3062  case Instruction::CallBr:
3063  case Instruction::Invoke:
3064  case Instruction::CleanupRet:
3065  case Instruction::CatchSwitch:
3066  case Instruction::AtomicRMW:
3067  case Instruction::AtomicCmpXchg:
3068  case Instruction::Br:
3069  case Instruction::Resume:
3070  case Instruction::Ret:
3071  case Instruction::Load:
3072  // The alignment of a pointer is interesting for loads.
3073  case Instruction::Store:
3074  // The alignment of a pointer is interesting for stores.
3075  case Instruction::Alloca:
3076  case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast:
3077  IsInterestingOpcode = true;
3078  }
3079  if (IsInterestingOpcode) {
3080  auto *&Insts = FI.OpcodeInstMap[I.getOpcode()];
3081  if (!Insts)
3082  Insts = new (Allocator) InstructionVectorTy();
3083  Insts->push_back(&I);
3084  }
3085  if (I.mayReadOrWriteMemory())
3086  FI.RWInsts.push_back(&I);
3087  }
3088 
3089  if (F.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::AlwaysInline) &&
3090  isInlineViable(F).isSuccess())
3091  InlineableFunctions.insert(&F);
3092 }

3133 void Attributor::identifyDefaultAbstractAttributes(Function &F) {
3134  if (!VisitedFunctions.insert(&F).second)
3135  return;
3136  if (F.isDeclaration())
3137  return;
3138 
3139  // In non-module runs we need to look at the call sites of a function to
3140  // determine if it is part of a must-tail call edge. This will influence what
3141  // attributes we can derive.
3142  InformationCache::FunctionInfo &FI = InfoCache.getFunctionInfo(F);
3143  if (!isModulePass() && !FI.CalledViaMustTail) {
3144  for (const Use &U : F.uses())
3145  if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(U.getUser()))

3149 
3150  IRPosition FPos = IRPosition::function(F);
3151

3153  // We need dead instruction detection because we do not want to deal with
3154  // broken IR in which SSA rules do not apply.
3155  getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(FPos);
3156 
3157  // Every function might be "will-return".

3159

3161  getOrCreateAAFor<AAUndefinedBehavior>(FPos);
3162

3164  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoUnwind>(FPos);
3165

3174

3176  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoRecurse>(FPos);
3177

3179  getOrCreateAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(FPos);
3180

3182  getOrCreateAAFor<AAMemoryLocation>(FPos);
3183 
3184  // Every function can track active assumptions.
3185  getOrCreateAAFor<AAAssumptionInfo>(FPos);
3186 
3187  // Every function might be applicable for Heap-To-Stack conversion.
3188  if (EnableHeapToStack)

3192  Type *ReturnType = F.getReturnType();

3194  // Argument attribute "returned" --- Create only one per function even
3195  // though it is an argument attribute.

3199 
3200  // Every returned value might be dead.
3201  getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(RetPos);
3202

3204  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
3205  getAssumedSimplified(RetPos, nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation,
3206  AA::Intraprocedural);
3207 
3208  // Every returned value might be marked noundef.
3209  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoUndef>(RetPos);
3210 
3211  if (ReturnType->isPointerTy()) {
3212 
3213  // Every function with pointer return type might be marked align.
3214  getOrCreateAAFor<AAAlign>(RetPos);
3215 
3216  // Every function with pointer return type might be marked nonnull.
3217  getOrCreateAAFor<AANonNull>(RetPos);
3218 
3219  // Every function with pointer return type might be marked noalias.
3220  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoAlias>(RetPos);
3221 
3222  // Every function with pointer return type might be marked
3223  // dereferenceable.
3224  getOrCreateAAFor<AADereferenceable>(RetPos);
3225  }

3234  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
3235  getAssumedSimplified(ArgPos, /* AA */ nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation,
3236  AA::Intraprocedural);
3237

3239  getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(ArgPos);
3240 
3241  // Every argument might be marked noundef.
3242  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoUndef>(ArgPos);
3243 
3244  if (Arg.getType()->isPointerTy()) {
3245  // Every argument with pointer type might be marked nonnull.
3246  getOrCreateAAFor<AANonNull>(ArgPos);
3247 
3248  // Every argument with pointer type might be marked noalias.
3249  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoAlias>(ArgPos);
3250

3252  getOrCreateAAFor<AADereferenceable>(ArgPos);
3253 
3254  // Every argument with pointer type might be marked align.
3255  getOrCreateAAFor<AAAlign>(ArgPos);
3256 
3257  // Every argument with pointer type might be marked nocapture.
3258  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoCapture>(ArgPos);
3259 
3260  // Every argument with pointer type might be marked

3263

3272  auto CallSitePred = [&](Instruction &I) -> bool {
3273  auto &CB = cast<CallBase>(I);
3274  IRPosition CBInstPos = IRPosition::inst(CB);
3275  IRPosition CBFnPos = IRPosition::callsite_function(CB);
3276 
3277  // Call sites might be dead if they do not have side effects and no live
3278  // users. The return value might be dead if there are no live users.
3279  getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(CBInstPos);
3280 
3281  Function *Callee = CB.getCalledFunction();
3282  // TODO: Even if the callee is not known now we might be able to simplify
3283  // the call/callee.
3284  if (!Callee)
3285  return true;
3286 
3287  // Every call site can track active assumptions.
3288  getOrCreateAAFor<AAAssumptionInfo>(CBFnPos);
3289 
3290  // Skip declarations except if annotations on their call sites were
3291  // explicitly requested.
3292  if (!AnnotateDeclarationCallSites && Callee->isDeclaration() &&
3293  !Callee->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_callback))
3294  return true;
3295 
3296  if (!Callee->getReturnType()->isVoidTy() && !CB.use_empty()) {
3297 
3298  IRPosition CBRetPos = IRPosition::callsite_returned(CB);
3299  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
3300  getAssumedSimplified(CBRetPos, nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation,
3301  AA::Intraprocedural);
3302  }
3303 
3304  for (int I = 0, E = CB.arg_size(); I < E; ++I) {
3305 
3306  IRPosition CBArgPos = IRPosition::callsite_argument(CB, I);
3307 
3308  // Every call site argument might be dead.
3309  getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(CBArgPos);
3310 
3311  // Call site argument might be simplified. We have to go through the
3312  // Attributor interface though as outside AAs can register custom
3313  // simplification callbacks.
3314  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
3315  getAssumedSimplified(CBArgPos, /* AA */ nullptr, UsedAssumedInformation,
3316  AA::Intraprocedural);
3317 
3318  // Every call site argument might be marked "noundef".
3319  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoUndef>(CBArgPos);
3320 
3321  if (!CB.getArgOperand(I)->getType()->isPointerTy())
3322  continue;
3323 
3324  // Call site argument attribute "non-null".
3325  getOrCreateAAFor<AANonNull>(CBArgPos);
3326 
3327  // Call site argument attribute "nocapture".
3328  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoCapture>(CBArgPos);
3329 
3330  // Call site argument attribute "no-alias".
3331  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoAlias>(CBArgPos);
3332 
3333  // Call site argument attribute "dereferenceable".
3334  getOrCreateAAFor<AADereferenceable>(CBArgPos);
3335 
3336  // Call site argument attribute "align".
3337  getOrCreateAAFor<AAAlign>(CBArgPos);
3338 
3339  // Call site argument attribute
3340  // "readnone/readonly/writeonly/..."
3341  getOrCreateAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(CBArgPos);
3342 
3343  // Call site argument attribute "nofree".
3344  getOrCreateAAFor<AANoFree>(CBArgPos);
3345  }
3346  return true;
3347  };

3349  auto &OpcodeInstMap = InfoCache.getOpcodeInstMapForFunction(F);
3350  bool Success;
3351  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
3352  Success = checkForAllInstructionsImpl(
3353  nullptr, OpcodeInstMap, CallSitePred, nullptr, nullptr,
3354  {(unsigned)Instruction::Invoke, (unsigned)Instruction::CallBr,
3355  (unsigned)Instruction::Call},
3356  UsedAssumedInformation);

3358  assert(Success && "Expected the check call to be successful!");

3360  auto LoadStorePred = [&](Instruction &I) -> bool {
3361  if (isa<LoadInst>(I)) {
3362  getOrCreateAAFor<AAAlign>(
3363  IRPosition::value(*cast<LoadInst>(I).getPointerOperand()));
3364  if (SimplifyAllLoads)
3365  getAssumedSimplified(IRPosition::value(I), nullptr,
3366  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Intraprocedural);

3369  getOrCreateAAFor<AAIsDead>(IRPosition::inst(I));

3371  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Intraprocedural);
3372  getOrCreateAAFor<AAAlign>(IRPosition::value(*SI.getPointerOperand()));
3373  }
3374  return true;
3375  };
3376  Success = checkForAllInstructionsImpl(
3377  nullptr, OpcodeInstMap, LoadStorePred, nullptr, nullptr,
3378  {(unsigned)Instruction::Load, (unsigned)Instruction::Store},
3379  UsedAssumedInformation);
3380  (void)Success;
3381  assert(Success && "Expected the check call to be successful!");
3382 }

3513  OS << " [" << **Acc.getContent() << "]";
3514  else
3515  OS << " [ <unknown> ]";
3516  }
3517  return OS;
3518 }
3519 ///}

3522 /// Pass (Manager) Boilerplate
3523 /// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3524 
3525 static bool runAttributorOnFunctions(InformationCache &InfoCache,
3526  SetVector<Function *> &Functions,
3527  AnalysisGetter &AG,
3528  CallGraphUpdater &CGUpdater,
3529  bool DeleteFns, bool IsModulePass) {
3530  if (Functions.empty())
3531  return false;
3532 
3533  LLVM_DEBUG({
3534  dbgs() << "[Attributor] Run on module with " << Functions.size()
3535  << " functions:\n";
3536  for (Function *Fn : Functions)
3537  dbgs() << " - " << Fn->getName() << "\n";
3538  });
3539 
3540  // Create an Attributor and initially empty information cache that is filled
3541  // while we identify default attribute opportunities.
3542  AttributorConfig AC(CGUpdater);
3543  AC.IsModulePass = IsModulePass;
3544  AC.DeleteFns = DeleteFns;
3545  Attributor A(Functions, InfoCache, AC);
3546 
3547  // Create shallow wrappers for all functions that are not IPO amendable
3548  if (AllowShallowWrappers)
3549  for (Function *F : Functions)
3550  if (!A.isFunctionIPOAmendable(*F))
3551  Attributor::createShallowWrapper(*F);
3552 
3553  // Internalize non-exact functions
3554  // TODO: for now we eagerly internalize functions without calculating the
3555  // cost, we need a cost interface to determine whether internalizing
3556  // a function is "beneficial"
3557  if (AllowDeepWrapper) {
3558  unsigned FunSize = Functions.size();
3559  for (unsigned u = 0; u < FunSize; u++) {
3560  Function *F = Functions[u];
3561  if (!F->isDeclaration() && !F->isDefinitionExact() && F->getNumUses() &&
3562  !GlobalValue::isInterposableLinkage(F->getLinkage())) {
3563  Function *NewF = Attributor::internalizeFunction(*F);
3564  assert(NewF && "Could not internalize function.");
3565  Functions.insert(NewF);
3566 
3567  // Update call graph
3568  CGUpdater.replaceFunctionWith(*F, *NewF);
3569  for (const Use &U : NewF->uses())
3570  if (CallBase *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(U.getUser())) {
3571  auto *CallerF = CB->getCaller();
3572  CGUpdater.reanalyzeFunction(*CallerF);
3573  }
3574  }
3575  }
3576  }
3577 
3578  for (Function *F : Functions) {
3579  if (F->hasExactDefinition())
3580  NumFnWithExactDefinition++;
3581  else
3582  NumFnWithoutExactDefinition++;
3583 
3584  // We look at internal functions only on-demand but if any use is not a
3585  // direct call or outside the current set of analyzed functions, we have
3586  // to do it eagerly.
3587  if (F->hasLocalLinkage()) {
3588  if (llvm::all_of(F->uses(), [&Functions](const Use &U) {
3589  const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(U.getUser());
3590  return CB && CB->isCallee(&U) &&
3591  Functions.count(const_cast<Function *>(CB->getCaller()));
3592  }))
3593  continue;
3594  }
3595 
3596  // Populate the Attributor with abstract attribute opportunities in the
3597  // function and the information cache with IR information.
3598  A.identifyDefaultAbstractAttributes(*F);
3599  }
3600 
3601  ChangeStatus Changed = A.run();
3602 
3603  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[Attributor] Done with " << Functions.size()
3604  << " functions, result: " << Changed << ".\n");
3605  return Changed == ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
3606 }

3637 PreservedAnalyses AttributorPass::run(Module &M, ModuleAnalysisManager &AM) {
3638  FunctionAnalysisManager &FAM =
3639  AM.getResult<FunctionAnalysisManagerModuleProxy>(M).getManager();
3640  AnalysisGetter AG(FAM);
3641 
3642  SetVector<Function *> Functions;
3643  for (Function &F : M)
3644  Functions.insert(&F);
3645 
3646  CallGraphUpdater CGUpdater;
3647  BumpPtrAllocator Allocator;

3649  if (runAttributorOnFunctions(InfoCache, Functions, AG, CGUpdater,
3650  /* DeleteFns */ true, /* IsModulePass */ true)) {

3657 PreservedAnalyses AttributorCGSCCPass::run(LazyCallGraph::SCC &C,
3658  CGSCCAnalysisManager &AM,
3659  LazyCallGraph &CG,
3660  CGSCCUpdateResult &UR) {
3661  FunctionAnalysisManager &FAM =
3662  AM.getResult<FunctionAnalysisManagerCGSCCProxy>(C, CG).getManager();
3663  AnalysisGetter AG(FAM);
3664 
3665  SetVector<Function *> Functions;
3666  for (LazyCallGraph::Node &N : C)
3667  Functions.insert(&N.getFunction());
3668 
3669  if (Functions.empty())
3670  return PreservedAnalyses::all();
3671 
3672  Module &M = *Functions.back()->getParent();
3673  CallGraphUpdater CGUpdater;
3674  CGUpdater.initialize(CG, C, AM, UR);
3675  BumpPtrAllocator Allocator;
3676  InformationCache InfoCache(M, AG, Allocator, /* CGSCC */ &Functions);
3677  if (runAttributorOnFunctions(InfoCache, Functions, AG, CGUpdater,
3678  /* DeleteFns */ false,
3679  /* IsModulePass */ false)) {
3680  // FIXME: Think about passes we will preserve and add them here.
3681  PreservedAnalyses PA;
3682  PA.preserve<FunctionAnalysisManagerCGSCCProxy>();
3683  return PA;
3684  }
3685  return PreservedAnalyses::all();
